  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Family of Elkanah'
      title: The Family of Elkanah
      number: 1
      content: 'There was a certain man from Ramathaim Zophim, from the hill country
        of Ephraim, whose name was Elkanah the son of Jeroham, the son of Elihu,
        the son of Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephraimite.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He had two wives; the name of the first was Hannah, and the name
        of the second was Peninnah. Now Peninnah had children, but Hannah had no
        children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now this man used to go up from his town year by year to worship
        and to sacrifice to Yahweh of hosts in Shiloh, where the two sons of Eli,
        Hophni and Phinehas, were priests to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the day Elkanah sacrificed, he would give portions to his wife
        Peninnah and to all her sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But to Hannah he would give a double portion, because he loved Hannah,
        though Yahweh had closed her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(Now her rival wife would provoke her severely in order to upset
        her because Yahweh had closed her womb.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And so he used to do year after year; whenever she went up to the
        house of Yahweh, she would provoke her so that she would weep and would not
        eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Elkanah her husband would say to her: \u201CHannah, why do you
        weep and why do you not eat? And why are you heartsick? Am I not better to
        you than ten sons?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Hannah got up after eating and drinking at Shiloh. (Now Eli
        the priest was sitting on his chair by the doorpost of the temple of Yahweh.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'She was deeply troubled, so she prayed to Yahweh and wept bitterly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "She made a vow and said: \u201CO Yahweh of hosts, if you will look
        with compassion on the misery of your female servant, and will remember me,
        and not forget your female servant, and will give to your female servant
        a male child then I will give him to Yahweh all the days of his life, and
        a razor will never pass over his head.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'While she continued to pray before Yahweh, Eli was observing her
        mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now Hannah had been speaking in her heart; her lips were moving,
        but her voice could not be heard, so Eli considered her to be drunk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Eli said to her, \u201CHow long will you behave like someone
        who is drunk? Put away your wine!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Hannah answered and said, \u201CNo, my lord. I am a woman deeply
        distressed, but I have not drunk wine or strong drink. Rather, I have poured
        out my soul before Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Do not regard your female servant as worthless, but because of the
        extent of my worries and my provocation I have spoken all of this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Eli answered and said, \u201CGo in peace, and may the God of
        Israel grant your request that you have asked of him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Birth of Samuel'
      title: The Birth of Samuel
      number: 18
      content: "And she said, \u201CMay your female slave find favor in your sight.\u201D
        Then the woman went on her way and ate something, and her face did not look
        sad any longer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then they rose early in the morning and worshiped before Yahweh and
        returned to their house at Ramah. Then Elkanah had sexual relations with
        Hannah his wife, and Yahweh remembered her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In due time, Hannah conceived and gave birth to a son. She called
        his name Samuel, for she said, \u201CI requested him from Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So the man Elkanah went up with all his household to make the annual
        sacrifice to Yahweh and to pay his vow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Hannah did not go up, for she said to her husband, \u201COnce
        the boy is weaned, I will bring him, so that he may appear before Yahweh;
        and he will remain there forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So her husband Elkanah said to her, \u201CDo what seems right to
        you; stay until you wean him. Only may Yahweh fulfill his word.\u201D So
        the woman remained and nursed her son until she weaned him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then she brought him up with her when she had weaned him, along with
        three bulls, one ephah of flour, and a skin of wine. She brought him to the
        house of Yahweh at Shiloh while the boy was still young. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'They slaughtered the bull, and they brought the boy to Eli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "She said, \u201CExcuse me, my lord. As you live, my lord, I am the
        woman who stood with you in this place to pray to Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'I prayed for this boy, and Yahweh has given me my request that I
        asked from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "I in turn have lent him to Yahweh. As long as he lives he is lent
        to Yahweh.\u201D Then they worshiped Yahweh there. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " Then Hannah prayed and said, \u201CMy heart exults in Yahweh, my
        strength is exalted in Yahweh; I grin over my enemies, for I rejoice over
        your salvation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There is no one holy like Yahweh, for there is no one besides you,
        and there is no rock like our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not increase speaking very proud words! Let no arrogance go forth
        from your mouth, for Yahweh is a God of knowledge whose deeds are not weighed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The bows of mighty warriors are shattered, but those who stumble
        gird themselves with strength. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Those who were full must hire themselves out for bread, but those
        who are hungry will become fat. As for the infertile, she will bear seven,
        but she who has many sons withers away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Yahweh kills and restores alive, he brings down to Sheol and raises
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yahweh makes poor and makes rich; he brings low and also exalts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He raises up the poor from the dust. From the ash heap he lifts up
        the needy, to cause them to sit with noble people and to cause them to inherit
        a seat of honor. For the pillars of the earth belong to Yahweh and he has
        set the inhabited world on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He will guard the feet of his faithful ones, but the wicked will
        be destroyed in the darkness, because a man will not prevail by his might. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yahweh will shatter his adversaries;  he will thunder against them
        in the heavens. Yahweh will judge the ends of the earth. He will give strength
        to his king and will exalt the might of his anointed one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Family of Eli the Priest'
      title: The Family of Eli the Priest
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Elkanah went to Ramah, to his house. Now the boy was serving
        Yahweh in the presence of Eli the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the sons of Eli were worthless scoundrels; they did not know
        Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the custom of the priests with the people was this: When any
        man brought a sacrifice, as the meat was boiling, the servant of the priest
        would take a three-pronged meat fork in his hand '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and would thrust it into the pan or into the kettle or into the cauldron
        or into the cooking pot. All that the meat fork brought up the priest would
        take for himself. This is what they used to do to all of the Israelites who
        came there at Shiloh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Also, before they offered up the fat as a burnt offering, the servant
        of the priest would come and say to the man who was sacrificing, \u201CGive
        the priest meat for roasting, for he will not take boiled meat from you,
        but only raw.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And if the man said to him, \u201CLet them burn the fat completely
        first, then take for yourself as you desire,\u201D then he would say to him,
        \u201CNo! Give it now! If not, I will take it by force!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Samuel\u2019s Life in the Tabernacle"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s Life in the Tabernacle"
      number: 17
      content: 'So the sin of the young men was very great in the sight of Yahweh,
        because the men treated the offering of Yahweh with contempt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now Samuel was serving before Yahweh, as a boy wearing a linen ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'His mother used to make for him a small robe and take it to him year
        by year whenever she came up with her husband to offer the annual sacrifice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Eli would bless Elkanah and his wife, and he said, \u201CMay
        Yahweh give you an offspring from this woman in place of the petitioned one
        that she requested from Yahweh.\u201D Then they went to their home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Eli Rebukes His Evil Sons'
      title: Eli Rebukes His Evil Sons
      number: 21
      content: 'Yahweh took note of Hannah, and she conceived and gave birth to three
        sons and two daughters, while the young man Samuel grew up with Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now Eli was very old, and he heard all that his sons were doing to
        all Israel and that they were having sexual relations with the women who
        were serving at the entrance of the tent of assembly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he asked them, \u201CWhy are you doing all these things that
        I am hearing, namely, your evil dealings with all these people? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'No, my sons, the report is not good that I am hearing the people
        of Yahweh spreading. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "If a man sins against a man, then God can intercede for him. But
        if a man sins against Yahweh, who can intercede for him?\u201D But they did
        not obey their father, because Yahweh wanted to kill them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Yahweh Rebukes Eli'
      title: Yahweh Rebukes Eli
      number: 26
      content: 'But the boy Samuel continued to grow in stature and in favor with
        Yahweh and with the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Now a man of God came to Eli and said to him: \u201CThus says Yahweh:
        \u2018Did I not clearly reveal myself to the house of your ancestor when
        they were in Egypt under the house of Pharaoh? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And I chose him from all the tribes of Israel to be a priest to me,
        to go up to my altar, to burn incense, and to bear an ephod before me. I
        gave to the house of your ancestor all the offerings made by fire by the
        Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Why do you despise my sacrifice and my offering which I commanded
        for my dwelling place, while you honored your sons more than me by making
        yourselves fat from the best of all the offerings of my people Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore,\u2019 declares Yahweh the God of Israel, \u2018though
        I solemnly said that your house and the house of your ancestor would walk
        before me forever, but now,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018far be it from me,
        for those who honor me I will honor, but those who despise me, I will treat
        with contempt! "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Look, days are coming when I will cut off your strength and the strength
        of the house of your ancestor so that no one in your house will live to old
        age.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'You will look at the distress of my dwelling place, despite all the
        good caused for Israel, but there will never be an old man in your household
        forever!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The only one I will not cut off from my altar is you. Rather, to
        cause your eyes to fail and to cause your soul to grieve, all the members
        of your household will die as men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'This is the sign for you that will come regarding your two sons Hophni
        and Phinehas: they will both die on the same day! '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But I will raise up for myself a reliable priest; he will do just
        according to what is in my heart and in my soul. I will build for him a lasting
        house and he will walk continually before my anointed one forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "All the remainder of your household will come to bow down before
        him for a bit of silver or a loaf of bread and will say, \u201CPlease assign
        me to one of the priestly offices so that I can eat a morsel of bread.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samuel\u2019s First Encounter with Yahweh"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s First Encounter with Yahweh"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the boy Samuel was serving Yahweh in the presence of Eli. The
        word of Yahweh was rare in those days; visions were not widespread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And then one day when Eli was lying in his place (now his eyes had
        begun to grow weak so that he was not able to see) '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the lamp of God had not yet gone out, Samuel was lying in the
        temple of Yahweh where the ark of God was. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Yahweh called out to Samuel and he said, \u201CHere I am!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he ran to Eli and said, \u201CHere I am, because you called me.\u201D
        But he said, \u201CI did not call you. Go back and lie down.\u201D So he
        went and lay down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Yahweh called Samuel again, so Samuel got up and went to Eli
        and said, \u201CHere I am, because you called me.\u201D And he said, \u201CI
        did not call you, my son. Go back and lie down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now Samuel did not yet know Yahweh, and the word of Yahweh had not
        yet been revealed to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Again Yahweh called Samuel a third time, so he got up and went to
        Eli and said, \u201CHere I am, because you called me.\u201D Then Eli realized
        that Yahweh was calling the boy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Eli said to Samuel \u201CGo lie down. If he calls to you, then
        you must say, \u2018Speak Yahweh, because your servant is listening.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        So Samuel went and lay down in his place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Yahweh came and stood there and called out as before, \u201CSamuel!
        Samuel!\u201D And Samuel said, \u201CSpeak, because your servant is listening.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Yahweh said to Samuel, \u201CLook, I am doing something in Israel
        which will cause the two ears of everyone who hears it to tingle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On that day I will fulfill against Eli all that I have spoken against
        his household, from beginning to end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will make him know that I am about to judge his household forever
        because of the iniquity that he knew, for his sons were bringing curses on
        themselves, but he did not rebuke them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore I swore to the house of Eli that the iniquity of the house
        of Eli would not be atoned for by sacrifice or by offering forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Samuel lay down until morning; then he opened the doors of the
        house of Yahweh, but Samuel was afraid of telling the vision to Eli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Eli called Samuel and said, \u201CSamuel, my son!\u201D And
        he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat is the message that he spoke to you? Please
        do not conceal it from me. May God punish you severely if you conceal anything
        from me of all the words that he told you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Samuel told him all the words and did not conceal anything from
        him. And he said, \u201CHe is Yahweh, he will do what is good in his sight.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Samuel grew up, and Yahweh was with him. He did not allow any
        of his prophecies to go unfulfilled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'All Israel from Dan to Beersheba realized that Samuel was faithful
        as a prophet to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Yahweh appeared again in Shiloh, for Yahweh revealed himself
        to Samuel in Shiloh through the word of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Battle of Aphek'
      title: The Battle of Aphek
      number: 1
      content: 'And the word of Samuel came to all Israel. Now Israel went out to
        meet the Philistines for battle, and they encamped at Ebenezer, and the Philistines
        encamped at Aphek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Philistines lined up for the battle to meet Israel, and the battle
        was prolonged until Israel was defeated before the Philistines, who killed
        about four thousand men on the battlefield.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When the army came back to the camp, the elders of Israel asked,
        \u201CWhy has Yahweh defeated us today before the Philistines? Let us bring
        the ark of the covenant of Yahweh to us from Shiloh so that it may come into
        our midst and deliver us from the hand of our enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the army sent to Shiloh and brought from there the ark of the
        covenant of Yahweh of hosts who sits between the cherubim. And the two sons
        of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were there with the ark of the covenant of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now when the ark of the covenant of Yahweh arrived at the camp, all
        Israel let out a loud shout so that the earth shook. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When the Philistines heard the noise of the shouting, they said,
        \u201CWhat is the noise of this loud shouting in the camp of the Hebrews?\u201D
        Then they learned that the ark of Yahweh had come into the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the Philistines were afraid, for they said, \u201CGod has come
        to the camp.\u201D And they said, \u201CWoe to us, for this has never happened
        before!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Woe to us! Who can deliver us from the hand of these mighty gods?
        These are the same gods who struck the Egyptians with all sorts of plagues
        in the desert. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Take courage and be men, you Philistines, lest you end up serving
        the Hebrews just like they have served you. Be men and fight!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the Philistines fought and Israel was defeated and each man fled
        to his tent, for the slaughter was very great. Thirty thousand foot soldiers
        from Israel fell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Furthermore, the ark of God was captured, and the two sons of Eli,
        Hophni and Phinehas, died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A man of Benjamin ran from the battle line and came to Shiloh that
        same day, and his clothes were torn and earth was on his head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he came, there was Eli sitting on his chair by the side of the
        road watching, because his heart was anxious about the ark of God. Now the
        man had come to give his report in the city, and all the city cried out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When Eli heard the noise of the outcry, he said, \u201CWhat is the
        noise of this commotion?\u201D Then the man came quickly and told Eli. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now Eli was ninety-eight years old and his eyes stayed fixed ahead
        and he was not able to see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the man said to Eli, \u201CI am the one who has come from the
        battle line! I have fled today from the battle line!\u201D And he said, \u201CWhat
        exactly happened, my son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the messenger answered and said, \u201CIsrael has fled before
        the Philistines. There has been a great defeat among the troops. Also, your
        two sons have died, Hophni and Phinehas, and the ark of God has been captured.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Just as he mentioned the ark of God, he fell from his chair backwards
        against the side of the gate. He broke his neck and died, because the man
        was old and heavy. He had judged Israel forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now his daughter-in-law, the wife of Phinehas, was pregnant and about
        to give birth. When she heard the news concerning the capture of the ark
        of God and that her father-in-law and her husband had died, she went into
        labor and gave birth, because her labor pains came upon her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Just before the time of her death, those attending her said, \u201CDo
        not fear, for you have given birth to a son.\u201D But she did not answer,
        or pay any attention.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "She called the boy Ichabod, saying, \u201CThe glory has departed
        from Israel,\u201D referring to the capture of the ark of God and concerning
        her father-in-law and husband. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And she said, \u201CThe glory has departed from Israel, because the
        ark of God was captured.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark of the Covenant among the Philistines'
      title: The Ark of the Covenant among the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the Philistines had captured the ark of God and brought it from
        Ebenezer to Ashdod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the Philistines took the ark of God and brought it to the temple
        of Dagon and placed it beside Dagon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When the Ashdodites got up early the next morning, there was Dagon
        fallen with his face to the ground before the ark of Yahweh! So they took
        Dagon and returned him to his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When they got up early in the morning the next day, there was Dagon
        fallen again with his face to the ground before the ark of Yahweh! The head
        of Dagon and the palms of his two hands were cut off, lying at the threshold;
        only the body of Dagon was left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '(Therefore the priests of Dagon and all who come into the house of
        Dagon do not tread on the threshold of Dagon in Ashdod until this very day.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now the hand of Yahweh was heavy against the Ashdodites and he destroyed
        them and struck them with tumors, both in Ashdod and its territories. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The men of Ashdod saw that it was so, and they said, \u201CThe ark
        of the God of Israel should not remain with us, because his hand is harsh
        on us and on Dagon our god!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So they sent and gathered all the rulers of the Philistines to them,
        and they asked, \u201CWhat shall we do with the ark of the God of Israel?\u201D
        And they said, \u201CLet the ark of the God of Israel be brought around toward
        Gath.\u201D So they moved the ark of the God of Israel to Gath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'After they moved it, the hand of Yahweh was against the city, causing
        a very great confusion, and he struck the men of the city from the youngest
        to the oldest, causing tumors to break out on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they sent the ark of God to Ekron. But when the ark of God came
        to Ekron, the Ekronites cried out, saying, \u201CThey have brought around
        the ark of the God of Israel to kill us and our people!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So they sent and gathered all the rulers of the Philistines, and
        they said, \u201CSend away the ark of the God of Israel and let it return
        to its place, so that it will not kill us and our people.\u201D For a deadly
        confusion was throughout all the city; the hand of God was very heavy there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The men who did not die were struck with the tumors, so that the
        cry of the city for help went up to heaven. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Return of the Ark of Covenant'
      title: The Return of the Ark of Covenant
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the ark of Yahweh had been in the territory of the Philistines
        for seven months, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and the Philistines called to the priests and to those who practiced
        divination, saying, \u201CWhat should we do with the ark of Yahweh? Inform
        us how we should send it to its place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said, \u201CIf you are sending the ark of the God of Israel
        away, you must not send it away empty, but by all means return it with a
        guilt offering. Then you will be healed and it will become known to you why
        his hand is not turned aside from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And they said, \u201CWhat is the guilt offering that we should return
        to him?\u201D They said, \u201CThe number of the rulers of the Philistines
        is five. Therefore send five gold tumors and five gold mice, because one
        plague was on all of you and all your rulers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You must make images of your tumors and images of your mice that
        are ravaging the land, and you must give glory to the God of Israel. Perhaps
        he will lighten his hand on you and on your gods and on your land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Why should you harden your hearts like the Egyptians and Pharaoh
        hardened their heart? Is it not just like when he dealt with them wantonly
        so that they sent them away and they left? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So then, prepare one new utility cart and two milking cows that have
        never had a yoke on them, and you must harness the cows to the utility cart
        and then turn their calves from following them to their stall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And you must take the ark of Yahweh and place it on the utility cart
        with the gold objects that you are returning to him as a guilt offering.
        You must place them in the container beside the ark and then send it off
        so that it goes away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You must watch; if it goes up by the way of its territory to Beth
        Shemesh, he has caused this great disaster to come on us. But if not, then
        we will know his hand has not struck us; it was by chance that this happened
        to us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the men did so; they took two milking cows and harnessed them
        to the utility cart, but they shut up their calves in the stall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then they put the ark of Yahweh on the utility cart with the container
        holding the gold mice and the images of their tumors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The cows went straight on the way on the road to Beth Shemesh, on
        the one main road, lowing as they went. They did not turn aside to the right
        or to the left, and the rulers of the Philistines were walking after them
        up to the border of Beth Shemesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the people of Beth Shemesh were reaping the wheat harvest in
        the valley. They lifted their eyes and saw the ark, and they were glad to
        see it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The utility cart came to the field of Joshua of Beth Shemesh and
        stopped there where there was a large stone. They split the wood of the utility
        cart and sacrificed the cows as a burnt offering to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the Levites took down the ark of Yahweh and the container that
        was beside it, in which were the gold objects, and they set them on the large
        stone. Then the men of Beth Shemesh offered burnt offerings, and they made
        sacrifices to Yahweh on that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The five rulers of the Philistines saw it and returned to Ekron that
        same day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now these are the gold tumors which the Philistines returned as a
        guilt offering to Yahweh: one for Ashdod, one for Gaza, one for Ashkelon,
        one for Gath, one for Ekron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the gold mice according to the number of all the cities of the
        Philistines, for their five rulers, from the fortified city to the unwalled
        village of the open country as far as the great stone, where they set the
        ark of Yahweh until this day in the field of Joshua of Beth Shemesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He struck seventy men among the men of Beth Shemesh because they
        looked into the ark of Yahweh. So the people mourned because Yahweh had struck
        a great blow among the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the men of Beth Shemesh asked, \u201CWho is able to stand before
        Yahweh, this holy God? And to whom shall it go up from us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So they sent messengers to the inhabitants of Kiriath Jearim saying,
        \u201CThe Philistines have returned the ark of Yahweh. Come down and take
        it up to yourselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Revival and Victory at Mizpah'
      title: Revival and Victory at Mizpah
      number: 1
      content: 'The men of Kiriath Jearim came and brought up the ark of Yahweh,
        and they brought it to the house of Abinadab in Gibeah. They consecrated
        Eleazer his son to guard the ark of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'From the day the ark stayed in Kiriath Jearim, days multiplied and
        became twenty years while all the house of Israel mourned after Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Samuel spoke to all the house of Israel, saying, \u201CIf with
        all your heart you are turning to Yahweh, remove the foreign gods and Ashtoreths
        from your midst. Commit your hearts to Yahweh and serve him alone. Then he
        will deliver you from the hand of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the Israelites removed the Baals and the Ashtoreths, and they
        served Yahweh alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Samuel said, \u201CGather all Israel to Mizpah, and I will pray
        to Yahweh for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So they gathered to Mizpah and drew water and poured it out before
        Yahweh. They fasted on that day and said there, \u201CWe have sinned against
        Yahweh!\u201D So Samuel judged the Israelites at Mizpah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now when the Philistines heard that the Israelites had gathered at
        Mizpah, the rulers of the Philistines went up against Israel. And when the
        Israelites heard of it, they were afraid of the Philistines.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the Israelites said to Samuel, \u201CYou must not cease from
        crying out to Yahweh our God, so that he will deliver us from the hand of
        the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Samuel took a single nursing lamb and sacrificed it as a whole
        burnt offering to Yahweh. Then Samuel cried out to Yahweh on behalf of Israel,
        and Yahweh answered him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'While Samuel was sacrificing the burnt offering, the Philistines
        drew near for the battle against Israel. But Yahweh thundered against the
        Philistines with a great noise on that day and threw them into confusion
        so that they were defeated before Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the men of Israel went out from Mizpah and pursued the Philistines
        and they struck them down as far as below Beth Car. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Samuel took a single stone and put it between Mizpah and Shen,
        and he named it Ebenezer and said, \u201CUp to here Yahweh has helped us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the Philistines were subdued and they did not come into the territory
        of Israel again, and the hand of Yahweh was against the Philistines all the
        days of Samuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Circuit Ministry of Samuel'
      title: The Circuit Ministry of Samuel
      number: 14
      content: 'The towns which the Philistines had taken from Israel were returned
        to Israel from Ekron to Gath, and Israel delivered their territories from
        the hand of the Philistines. Then there was peace between Israel and the
        Amorites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Samuel judged Israel all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He used to go on the circuit from year to year. He went around Bethel,
        Gilgal, and Mizpah, and he judged Israel in all these places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then he returned to Ramah, because his house was there, and there
        he judged Israel, and he built an altar to Yahweh there. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Demand for a King"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Demand for a King"
      number: 1
      content: 'When Samuel grew old he appointed his sons as judges over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The name of his firstborn son was Joel, and the name of his second
        son was Abijah. They were judges in Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But his sons did not walk in his ways; they turned aside after gain,
        they took bribes, and they perverted justice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So all the elders of Israel gathered together and came to Samuel
        at Ramah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They said to him, \u201CLook, you are old and your sons do not follow
        in your ways. So then appoint a king for us to judge us, like all the nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But the matter was displeasing to Samuel when they said, \u201CGive
        us a king to judge us,\u201D so Samuel prayed to Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Samuel, \u201CListen to the voice of the people
        concerning all that they say to you; for they have not rejected you, but
        they have rejected me from being king over them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Like all the deeds they have done from the day I brought them up
        from Egypt until this day, they have forsaken me and have served other gods\u2014so
        they are doing to you also. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And so then, listen to their voice. However, you must earnestly warn
        them; you must explain to them the custom of the king who will rule over
        them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Samuel spoke all the words of Yahweh to the people who were requesting
        a king from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said, \u201CThis will be the custom of the king who will reign
        over you: he will take your sons and appoint them to his chariots and his
        horsemen, and they will run before his chariots. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He will appoint for himself commanders of thousands and commanders
        of fifties, and those to do his plowing and to reap his harvest, and those
        to make weapons of war and the equipment for his chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will take your daughters as his perfume makers and as cooks and
        as bakers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He will take the best of your fields and your vineyards and your
        olive trees and will give them to his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He will take a tenth of your seed and your vineyards and give it
        to his high officials and to his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He will take your male slaves and your female slaves and the best
        of your young men and your donkeys and will use them for his projects.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He will take a tenth of your flocks, and you yourselves will become
        his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So you will cry out on that day because of your king whom you have
        chosen for yourselves, but Yahweh will not answer you on that day!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "However, the people refused to listen to the voice of Samuel and
        they said, \u201CNo, but there must be a king over us, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "so that we also may be like all the nations, and our king may rule
        us and go out before us and fight our battles.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now when Samuel heard all the words of the people, he repeated them
        in the ears of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Samuel, \u201CListen to their voice, and appoint
        a king for them.\u201D So Samuel spoke to the men of Israel, \u201CEach of
        you go to his own town.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul, the Requested King, Introduced'
      title: Saul, the Requested King, Introduced
      number: 1
      content: 'Now there was a man from Benjamin whose name was Kish, the son of
        Abiel, the son of Zeror, the son of Becorath, the son of Aphiah, the son
        of a Benjaminite, a very wealthy man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He had a son whose name was Saul, a young and handsome man. There
        was not a man from the Israelites more handsome than he was; from his shoulders
        up, he was taller than all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now the female donkeys of Kish the father of Saul got lost, and Kish
        said to Saul his son, \u201CPlease take one of the servants with you and
        get up; go and seek the female donkeys.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So he passed through the hill country of Ephraim; he passed through
        the land of Shalisha but they did not find them. They passed through the
        land of Shaalim but they were not there. He passed through the land of Benjamin
        but did not find them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When they entered the land of Zuph, Saul said to his servant who
        was with him, \u201CCome, let us return, lest my father cease caring about
        the female donkeys and worry about us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But he said to him, \u201CLook, a man of God is in this town, and
        the man is honored. All that he says certainly comes true. So then let us
        go there; perhaps he will tell us about our journey on which we have gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Saul said to his servant, \u201CLook, we may go, but what should
        we bring to the man? For the bread is gone from our bags, and there is no
        present to bring to the man of God. What do we have with us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The servant again answered Saul and said, \u201CLook, I have in my
        hand a quarter shekel of silver! I will give it to the man of God so that
        he will tell us our way.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "(Formerly in Israel, when a man went to inquire of God, he would
        say: \u201CCome, let us go up to the seer.\u201D For the prophet of today
        was formerly called a seer.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Saul said to his servant, \u201CYour suggestion is a good one.
        Come, let us go.\u201D And they went to the town where the man of God was. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "They were going up the ascent of the town when they found young women
        going out to draw water. They said to them, \u201CIs there the seer here?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They answered them and said, \u201CThere is. Look, he is just in
        front of you! Hurry now, because he has come to the town today, because there
        is a sacrifice for the people today at the high place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As soon as you enter the town, you will find him, before he goes
        up to the high place to eat. For the people will not eat until he comes,
        because he must bless the sacrifice. Then afterward the invited guests will
        eat. So then, go up, because you will find him today!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So they went up to the town. As they were entering into the middle
        of the town, Samuel was coming forth to meet them, to go up to the high place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now Yahweh had revealed this to Samuel the day before Saul arrived,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThis time tomorrow I will send to you a man from the land of
        Benjamin, and you must anoint him as leader over my people Israel. He will
        deliver my people from the hand of the Philistines. For I have seen the suffering
        of my people, because their cry of distress has come to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Samuel saw Saul, Yahweh answered him, \u201CHere is the man
        about whom I told you! This is the one who will govern my people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Saul approached Samuel in the middle of the gate and said, \u201CPlease
        tell me, where is the house of the seer?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Samuel answered Saul and said, \u201CI am the seer. Go up ahead of
        me to the high place, and you will eat with me today; then I will send you
        away in the morning. I will tell you all that is on your mind.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And as for your female donkeys that were lost three days ago, do
        not be concerned about them, because they have been found. For whom is all
        the desire of Israel? Is it not for you and for all the house of your father?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Saul answered and said, \u201CAm I not a Benjaminite, from the smallest
        of the tribes of Israel, and my family the humblest of all the families of
        the tribes of Benjamin? Why do you speak to me in this way?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Samuel took Saul and his servant and brought them to a room in
        the building and gave them a place at the head of the invited guests. There
        were about thirty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Samuel said to the cook, \u201CBring the portion that I gave
        to you, about which I said to you, \u2018Keep it with you.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So the cook took up the shank and what was on it and put it before
        Saul, and he said, \u201CLook, the saved portion is placed before you\u2014eat,
        because it has been kept for you for the appointed time,\u201D and he said,
        \u201CI have invited the people.\u201D So Saul ate with Samuel that day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When they came down from the high place to the town, he spoke with
        Saul on the roof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "They got up early, and as dawn was breaking, Samuel called to Saul
        on the roof, saying, \u201CGet up, so that I can send you away.\u201D So
        Saul got up and the two of them, he and Samuel, went outside. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "As they were going down to the outskirts of the town, Samuel said
        to Saul, \u201CTell the servant to pass on before us. When he has passed,
        you stand here a while, so that I can make known to you the word of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Is Anointed as King'
      title: Saul Is Anointed as King
      number: 1
      content: "Then Samuel took a flask of oil and poured it over his head and kissed
        him and said, \u201CHas not Yahweh anointed you as leader over his inheritance? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "As you go from with me today, you will find two men near the burial
        site of Rachel in the territory of Benjamin at Zelzah. They will say to you,
        \u2018The female donkeys that you went to search for have been found.\u2019
        Now look, your father is no longer concerned about the female donkeys and
        has begun worrying about you, saying, \u2018What should I do about my son?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then you will go on from there and further you will come to the oak
        of Tabor. There three men will meet you, who are going up to God at Bethel.
        One will be carrying three male kid goats, one will be carrying three loaves
        of bread, and one will be carrying a skin of wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They will ask how you are doing and will give you two loaves, which
        you will take from their hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'After this, you will come to the Gibeah of God, where there are sentries
        of the Philistines. Just as you enter the town there, you will meet a procession
        of prophets coming down from the high place, with harp, tambourine, flute,
        and zither before them, and they will be prophesying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Spirit of Yahweh will rush upon you, and you will prophesy
        with them; and you will turn into a different person.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When these signs come to you, do for yourself what your hand finds
        to do, for God will be with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then you will go down before me to Gilgal. Look, I am coming down
        to you to offer burnt offerings and to make fellowship offerings. You must
        wait seven days until I come to you. Then I will let you know what you should
        do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Just as he turned his shoulder to depart from Samuel, God changed
        his heart. And all these signs were fulfilled on that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they went from there to Gibeah, a procession of prophets met
        him, and the Spirit of God rushed upon him, and he prophesied among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And when all who knew him formerly saw that he prophesied with prophets,
        the people said to one another, \u201CWhat is this that has happened to the
        son of Kish? Is Saul also among the prophets?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And a man from there responded and said, \u201CAnd who is their father?\u201D
        Therefore it became a proverb: \u201CIs Saul also among the prophets?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he finished prophesying, he went to the high place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Saul\u2019s uncle said to him and to his servant, \u201CWhere
        did you go?\u201D And he said, \u201CTo search for the female donkeys; and
        when we saw none, we went to Samuel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So Saul\u2019s uncle said to him, \u201CPlease tell me, what did
        Samuel say to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Saul said to his uncle, \u201CHe told us for certain that the
        female donkeys had been found.\u201D But he did not tell him about the matter
        of the kingship of which Samuel had spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Samuel summoned the people to Yahweh at Mizpah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and he said to the Israelites, \u201CThus says Yahweh the God of
        Israel: \u2018I brought Israel up from Egypt, and I delivered you from the
        hand of the Egyptians and from the hand of all the kingdoms that were oppressing
        you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But you today have rejected your God who always delivers you from
        all of your calamities and your distresses. You have said to him, \u2018No,
        but you must appoint a king over us!\u2019 So then present yourselves before
        Yahweh by your tribes and by your clans.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Samuel brought near all the tribes of Israel, and the tribe of
        Benjamin was selected by lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then he brought near the tribe of Benjamin according to its families,
        and the family of Matri was selected by lot. Then Saul the son of Kish was
        chosen, and they sought him, but he could not be found. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So they inquired again of Yahweh, \u201CDid the man come here?\u201D 
        And Yahweh said, \u201CLook, he is hiding himself among the baggage.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So they ran and took him from there, and when he took his stand among
        the people, he was taller than all the people from his shoulders and up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Samuel said to all the people, \u201CDo you see him whom Yahweh
        has chosen? For there is no one like him among all the people!\u201D And
        all the people shouted and said, \u201CLong live the king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Samuel told the people the custom of the kingship, and he wrote
        the rules down on a scroll and laid it before Yahweh. Then Samuel sent all
        the people away, each to his own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Saul also went to his house at Gibeah, and the troops whose hearts
        God had touched went with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "However, some worthless men said, \u201CHow can this man deliver
        us?\u201D So they despised him and brought no gift to him, but he kept silent.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Defeats the Ammonites'
      title: Saul Defeats the Ammonites
      number: 1
      content: "Now Nahash the Ammonite went up and encamped against Jabesh Gilead.
        All the men of Jabesh said to Nahash, \u201CMake a treaty with us and we
        will serve you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Nahash the Ammonite said to them, \u201COn this condition I will
        make a treaty with you, by gouging out the right eye of each of you, so that
        I can make it a disgrace for all Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So the elders of Jabesh said to him, \u201CLeave us alone for seven
        days so that we may send messengers in all the territory of Israel, and if
        there is no deliverer for us, then we will come out to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the messengers came to Gibeah of Saul, they reported these things
        to the people. Then all the people lifted up their voices and wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Just then, Saul was coming from the field behind the cattle. Saul
        said, \u201CWhat is the matter with the people, that they are weeping?\u201D
        So they recounted to him the words of the men of Jabesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Spirit of God rushed upon Saul when he heard these words,
        and he became very angry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So he took a yoke of oxen and cut them into pieces and sent them
        throughout all the territory of Israel by the hand of the messengers, saying,
        \u201CWhoever is not going out after Saul and after Samuel, so will it be
        done to his oxen.\u201D Then the fear of Yahweh fell on the people and they
        went out as one man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He mustered them at Bezek; the Israelites were three hundred thousand,
        and the men of Judah were thirty thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They said to the messengers who had come, \u201CThus you will say
        to the men of Jabesh Gilead: \u2018Tomorrow deliverance for you will come
        when the sun is hot.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D When the messengers went and told
        the men of Jabesh, they rejoiced. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The men of Jabesh said, \u201CTomorrow we will come out to you and
        you may do to us whatever seems good to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the next day Saul placed the people in three divisions. Then
        they came into the middle of the camp at the early morning watch and struck
        down the Ammonites until the heat of the day. It happened that the remainder
        were scattered so that no two among them remained together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the people said to Samuel, \u201CWho is the one who asked, \u2018Will
        Saul reign over us?\u2019 Give the men to us that we may kill them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Saul said, \u201CNo one will be put to death on this day, because
        today Yahweh has provided deliverance in Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Samuel said to the people, \u201CCome, let us go to Gilgal,
        and let us renew the kingship there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So all the people went to Gilgal and they made Saul king there before
        Yahweh in Gilgal. They sacrificed fellowship offerings there before Yahweh.
        Then Saul rejoiced there greatly along with all the men of Israel. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samuel\u2019s Charge to Israel"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s Charge to Israel"
      number: 1
      content: "Then Samuel said to all Israel, \u201CLook, I have listened to your
        voice regarding all that you have said to me, so I have set a king over you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And so then here is the king walking about before you. Now I am old
        and gray, but my sons (look at them!) are with you; and I have walked about
        before you from my youth until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Here I am! Testify against me before Yahweh and before his anointed
        one! Whose ox have I taken? Or whose donkey have I taken? Or whom have I
        exploited? Whom have I oppressed? Or from whose hand have I taken a bribe,
        that I may shut my eyes regarding him?\u2013then I will restore it to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then they said, \u201CYou have not exploited us or oppressed us,
        and you have not taken anything from the hand of anyone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So he said to them, \u201CYahweh is witness against you, and his
        anointed one is witness this day, that you have not found anything in my
        hand.\u201D Then they said, \u201CHe is witness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Samuel said to the people, \u201CYahweh is witness, who appointed
        Moses and Aaron, and who brought your ancestors up from the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So then take your stand, so that I may judge you before Yahweh with
        regard to all the deeds of justice of Yahweh that he performed with both
        you and your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWhen Jacob came to Egypt, your ancestors cried out to Yahweh,
        so he sent Moses and Aaron, and they brought your ancestors out from Egypt
        and settled them in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But they forgot Yahweh their God, so he sold them into the hand of
        Sisera, commander of the hosts of Hazor, and into the hand of the Philistines,
        and into the hand of the king of Moab, and they fought against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they cried out to Yahweh and said, \u2018We have sinned, because
        we have forsaken Yahweh and have served the Baals and the Ashtoreths. But
        now deliver us from the hand of our enemies and we will serve you!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Yahweh sent Jerub-Baal and Bedan and Jephthah and Samuel. Then
        he delivered you from the hand of your enemies all around, and you lived
        in security. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd when you saw that Nahash, the king of the Ammonites, was
        coming against you, you said to me, \u2018No! A king shall reign over us,\u2019
        although Yahweh your God is your king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So then look! Here is the king you have chosen, for whom you have
        asked! Look, Yahweh has placed a king over you! '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If you will fear Yahweh, and serve him, and listen to his voice,
        and not be rebellious against what Yahweh says, and both you and the king
        who rules over you will follow after Yahweh your God, all will be well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But, if you do not listen to the voice of Yahweh, and you rebel against
        what Yahweh says, then the hand of Yahweh will be against you as it was against
        your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So then take your stand again and see this great thing that Yahweh
        is going to do before your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Is the wheat harvest not today? I will call out to Yahweh so that
        he still sends thunder and rain, so that you will know and will see that
        your wickedness is great that you have done in the eyes of Yahweh by asking
        for a king for yourselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Samuel called out to Yahweh, and Yahweh brought thunder and rain
        that same day, so all the people feared Yahweh and Samuel greatly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then all the people said to Samuel, \u201CPray for your servants
        to Yahweh your God so that we will not die, because we have added to all
        our sins by requesting a king for ourselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Samuel said to the people, \u201CDo not fear! You have done all
        this evil; only do not turn aside from following Yahweh. But you must serve
        Yahweh with all your heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And do not turn aside after the triviality, which have no value and
        cannot deliver, for they are triviality. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For Yahweh will not forsake his people for the sake of his great
        name, because Yahweh has decided to make you his own people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Also, as for me, far be it from me that I should sin against Yahweh
        by ceasing to pray for you! I will instruct you in the good and righteous
        way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Only fear Yahweh and serve him faithfully with all of your heart.
        For consider what great things he has done for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But if you continue to do wickedness, both you and your king will
        be swept away.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Rules over Israel'
      title: Saul Rules over Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Saul was thirty years old at the beginning of his reign, and he reigned
        forty-two years over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He chose for himself three thousand from Israel. Two thousand of
        these were with Saul at Micmash in the hill country of Bethel, and a thousand
        were with Jonathan at Gibeah in Benjamin. He sent away the rest of the people,
        each to his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jonathan defeated the garrison of the Philistines that was at Geba,
        and the Philistines heard about it. Then Saul blew the trumpet throughout
        all the land, saying, \u201CLet the Hebrews hear!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "4: Saul\u2019s Blunder"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Blunder"
      number: 4
      content: "And all Israel did hear, saying, \u201CSaul has defeated the garrison
        of the Philistines; and also, Israel has become a stench among the Philistines!\u201D
        So the people were called out after Saul at Gilgal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the Philistines assembled to fight with Israel, thirty thousand
        chariots and six thousand horsemen and an army as numerous as sand which
        is on the seashore. And they came up and encamped at Micmash, east of Beth
        Aven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the men of Israel saw that it was too difficult for them, because
        the army was hard pressed, the people hid themselves in the caves, in the
        thorn bushes, in the cliffs, in the vaults and in the wells. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Some of the Hebrews crossed over the Jordan to the land of Gad and
        Gilead. But Saul was still at Gilgal, and all the army followed him trembling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He waited seven days according to the appointed time Samuel determined,
        but Samuel did not come to Gilgal, and the army started to slip away from
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Saul said, \u201CBring here to me the burnt offering and the fellowship
        offerings.\u201D Then he offered up the burnt offering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Just as he finished offering the burnt sacrifice, Samuel was coming.
        So Saul went out to meet him and to bless him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Samuel said, \u201CWhat have you done?\u201D Saul said, \u201CBecause
        I saw that the army was scattering from me and you did not come at the appointed
        time and that the Philistines had gathered at Micmash, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "therefore I said, \u2018Now the Philistines will come down against
        me at Gilgal, and I have not yet implored the face of Yahweh.\u2019 So I
        forced myself and offered the burnt offering.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201CYou have behaved foolishly! You have
        not kept the command of Yahweh your God which he commanded you. For then,
        Yahweh would have established your kingdom over Israel forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But now, your kingdom will not endure. Yahweh has sought for himself
        a man according to his own heart, and Yahweh has appointed him as leader
        over his people, because you have not kept what Yahweh commanded you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Samuel got up and went up from Gilgal to Gibeah of Benjamin.
        And Saul mustered the people who were found with him, about six hundred men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Saul and Jonathan his son and the army that remained with them were
        staying in Geba of Benjamin, and the Philistines encamped at Micmash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The raiders went out from the camp of the Philistines in three divisions.
        One division turned on the road to Ophrah toward the land of Shual. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'One division turned on the road to Beth Horon, and one turned on
        the road toward the border overlooking the valley of Zeboim toward the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now no skilled craftsman could be found in all the land of Israel,
        for the Philistines had said, \u201CSo that the Hebrews cannot make swords
        or spears for themselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So all Israel went down to the Philistines, each to have his plowshare,
        his mattock, his axe, and his iron plowshare sharpened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The charge was two-thirds of a shekel for the plowshare and for the
        mattock, and a third of a shekel for the pick and for the axe, and to set
        the goading sticks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So on the day of battle, there was not a sword or a spear found in
        the hands of all the army that was with Saul and Jonathan, but Saul and his
        son Jonathan had them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now the garrison of the Philistines went out to the pass of Micmash. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jonathan Leads the Counterattack'
      title: Jonathan Leads the Counterattack
      number: 1
      content: "One day Jonathan the son of Saul said to his armor bearer, \u201CCome
        and let us go over to the garrison of the Philistines which is over there.\u201D
        But he did not tell his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now Saul was staying at the outskirts of Gibeah under the pomegranate
        tree that was in Migron, and the troops that were with him were about six
        hundred men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Ahijah, the son of Ahitub (the brother of Ichabod), the son of
        Phinehas, the son of Eli the priest of Yahweh at Shiloh, was carrying an
        ephod. The troops did not know that Jonathan had gone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now between the passes where Jonathan sought to go over to the garrison
        of the Philistines there was a crag of rock on one side and a crag of rock
        on the other. The name of the one was Bozez and the name of the other was
        Seneh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The one crag on the north was opposite Micmash and the other on the
        south was opposite Geba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Jonathan said to his armor bearer, \u201CCome, let us go over
        to the garrisons of these uncircumcised; perhaps Yahweh will act for us,
        for there is no hindrance for Yahweh to save by many or by few.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And his armor bearer said, \u201CDo all that is in your heart that
        you are inclined to do. I am with you all of the way!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Jonathan said, \u201CLook, we are about to go over to the men;
        and we will show ourselves to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If they say to us: \u2018Wait until we reach you,\u2019 then we will
        stand as we are and not go up to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But if they say, \u2018Come up to us,\u2019 then we will go up, for
        Yahweh has given them into our hand, and this will be the sign for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the two of them showed themselves to the garrison of the Philistines,
        and the Philistines said, \u201CThe Hebrews are coming out from the holes
        in which they have hidden themselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the men of the garrison answered Jonathan and his armor bearer,
        \u201CCome up to us and we will show you something!\u201D Then Jonathan said
        to his armor bearer, \u201CCome up after me, for Yahweh has given them into
        the hand of Israel!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Jonathan went up on his hands and his feet, with his armor bearer
        after him. They fell before Jonathan and then his armor bearer would kill
        them after him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So was the first attack in which Jonathan and his armor bearer killed
        about twenty men within about half of a furrow in an acre of an open field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then there was terror in the camp, in the open field, and among all
        the army of the garrison. Even the raiders trembled. The earth shook, and
        it became a very great panic.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the lookouts of Saul in Gibeah of Benjamin saw that the multitude
        surged back and forth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Saul said to the troops that were with him, \u201CPlease call the
        roll and see who has gone from us.\u201D So they called the roll and found
        that Jonathan and his armor bearer were not present. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Saul said to Ahijah, \u201CBring near the ark of God\u201D (for
        the ark of God was at that time with the Israelites).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "While Saul was still speaking to the priest, the tumult in the camp
        of the Philistines increased more and more, so Saul said to the priest, \u201CWithdraw
        your hand!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Saul and all the troops who were with him were assembled on
        command and came up to the battle, and look! Each Philistine\u2019s sword
        was against his friend; and there was a very great confusion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The Hebrews who had been for the Philistines previously, who had
        gone up with them into the camp all around, even they joined the Israelites
        who were with Saul and Jonathan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'All the men of Israel who had hidden themselves in the hill country
        of Ephraim heard that the Philistines had fled, so even they pursued them
        closely in the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Saul\u2019s Oath Leads to Trouble"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Oath Leads to Trouble"
      number: 23
      content: 'So on that day Yahweh delivered Israel, and the battle shifted to
        Beth Aven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Now the men of Israel were hard pressed on that day, because Saul
        had made the army take an oath, saying, \u201CCursed be the man who eats
        any food until evening, when I will have avenged myself on my enemies!\u201D
        So none of the army tasted any food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '(Now all the people of the land used to go into the forest, for there
        was honey on the surface of the ground.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When the army came to the forest, look! There was honey flowing,
        but no one put his hand to his mouth, for the army was afraid of the solemn
        oath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'However, Jonathan had not heard about the oath of his father with
        the army, so he extended the end of the staff which was in his hand, and
        he dipped it into the honeycomb. Then he put his hand to his mouth and his
        eyes gleamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then a man from the army informed him and said, \u201CYour father
        made the army swear a solemn oath, saying, \u2018Cursed be the man who eats
        food today,\u2019&nbsp;\u201D so the army is exhausted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Jonathan said, \u201CMy father has brought trouble on the land!
        See now that my eyes have brightened because I have tasted a little of this
        honey. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "How much more could have been done if the troops had eaten freely
        today from the plunder of their enemies that they had found! For now the
        loss among the Philistines is not great.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'They defeated the Philistines that day from Micmash to Aijalon, and
        the troops were very weary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then the troops took the plunder: they took sheep and cattle and
        calves and slaughtered them on the ground and the troops ate them all with
        the blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So they reported it to Saul, saying, \u201CLook! The troops are sinning
        against Yahweh by eating the animals with the blood!\u201D And he said, \u201CYou
        have dealt treacherously! Roll to me a large stone today!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Jonathan Rescued from His Father Saul'
      title: Jonathan Rescued from His Father Saul
      number: 34
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CDisperse yourselves among the troops and say
        to them, \u2018Bring to me each one his ox and each his sheep and slaughter
        them in this place and eat, but do not sin against Yahweh by eating the animals
        with the blood.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D So all the troops brought them, each leading
        his ox in his hand that night, and slaughtered it there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then Saul built an altar to Yahweh; it was the first altar he built
        to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Saul said, \u201CLet us go down after the Philistines by night, and
        let us plunder them until the morning light, and let us not leave alive a
        man among them.\u201D So they said, \u201CDo all that is good in your eyes.\u201D
        But the priest said, \u201CLet us draw near to God here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So Saul inquired of God, \u201CShould I go down after the Philistines?
        Will you give them into the hand of Israel?\u201D But he did not answer him
        on that day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CCome here, all you leaders of the people, so
        that we find out what the sin was this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "For as Yahweh lives, who delivers Israel, I swear that even if it
        is in Jonathan my son, he will certainly die!\u201D But nobody from all the
        army answered him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then he said to all Israel, \u201CYou will be on one side, and I
        and my son Jonathan will be on the other.\u201D And the army said to Saul,
        \u201CDo what is good in your eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then Saul said to Yahweh the God of Israel, \u201CRender a decision
        perfectly.\u201D Jonathan and Saul were chosen by lot and the people went
        out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CLet them cast the lot between me and my son
        Jonathan,\u201D and Jonathan was chosen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "So Saul said, \u201CTell me what you have done.\u201D So Jonathan
        told him and said, \u201CI merely tasted a little honey with the end of the
        staff that was in my hand. Here I am, I must die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CSo may God do to me and more, you will certainly
        die today, Jonathan!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "But the army said to Saul, \u201CMust Jonathan die, who accomplished
        this great victory in Israel? Far from it! As Yahweh lives, not a hair from
        his head will fall to the ground, for he has worked with God this day.\u201D
        So the army ransomed Jonathan and he did not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Saul went up from pursuing the Philistines, and the Philistines went
        to their place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'So Saul took the kingship over Israel, and he fought all around against
        his enemies, against Moab, against the Ammonites, against Edom, against the
        kings of Zobah, and against the Philistines. He inflicted punishment against
        all who rebelled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'He acted bravely and defeated the Amalekites and rescued Israel from
        the hand of those who plundered it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Now the sons of Saul were Jonathan, Ishvi, and Malki-Shua; the names
        of his two daughters were as follows: the name of the firstborn was Merab
        and the younger was Michal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "The name of Saul\u2019s wife was Ahinoam the daughter of Ahimaaz,
        and the name of the commander of his army was Abner, the son of Ner, Saul\u2019s
        uncle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Now Kish was the father of Saul, but Ner, the father of Abner, was
        the son of Abiel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Warfare was severe against the Philistines all the days of Saul.
        Whenever Saul saw anyone who was a mighty warrior or any brave man, he conscripted
        him into his service.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Defeats the Amalekites'
      title: Israel Defeats the Amalekites
      number: 1
      content: "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201CYahweh sent me to anoint you as king
        over his people Israel. So then, listen to the words of Yahweh! "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u2018I have observed what Amalek did
        to Israel, how he opposed him when he went up from Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So then, go and attack Amalek and utterly destroy all that is his!
        You must not spare him, but kill both man and woman, both child and nursing
        infant, both ox and sheep, both camel and donkey.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Saul summoned the army and mustered them at Telaim; two hundred thousand
        foot soldiers and ten thousand men of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Saul came up to the city of Amalek and set an ambush in the
        wadi.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Saul said to the Kenites, \u201CGo, leave! Withdraw from among the
        Amalekites so that I do not destroy you with them. You have shown loyal love
        to all the Israelites when they came up from Egypt.\u201D So the Kenites
        left from among the Amalekites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Saul defeated the Amalekites from Havilah as one goes to Shur
        which is east of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He captured Agag the king of Amalek alive, but all the people he
        utterly destroyed with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Samuel Announces the Downfall of Saul'
      title: Samuel Announces the Downfall of Saul
      number: 9
      content: 'However, Saul and the army spared Agag and the best of the sheep
        and the cattle and the second best of the young fatlings and all that was
        valuable; they were not willing to utterly destroy them. But all the possessions
        that were despised or worthless, they utterly destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the word of Yahweh came to Samuel, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI regret that I made Saul king, for he has turned back from
        following me and has not kept my word.\u201D Samuel became angry, and he
        cried out to Yahweh all night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Samuel got up early in the morning to meet Saul. Samuel was
        told, \u201CSaul has gone to Carmel, and look, he is setting up a monument
        for himself.\u201D Then he turned around and crossed over and went down to
        Gilgal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When Samuel came to Saul, Saul said to him, \u201CMay you be blessed
        by Yahweh! I have kept the word of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Samuel said, \u201CThen what is this bleating of the sheep that
        I hear in my ears and the lowing of the cattle that I am hearing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Saul said, \u201CThey have brought them from the Amalekites; the
        troops spared the best of the sheep and the cattle in order to sacrifice
        them to Yahweh your God. But the rest we have utterly destroyed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201CStop and let me tell you what Yahweh
        said to me last night.\u201D So he said to him, \u201CSpeak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Samuel said, \u201CEven though you are small in your own eyes, are
        you not the head of the tribes of Israel? Yahweh has anointed you as king
        over Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When Yahweh sent you on your way, he said to you: \u2018Go! You must
        utterly destroy the sinners, the Amalekites, and you must fight against them
        until you have destroyed them.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why did you not listen to the voice of Yahweh and fall with shouting
        on the plunder? You have done evil in the sight of Yahweh!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Saul said to Samuel, \u201CI have listened to the voice of Yahweh,
        and I have gone on the way that Yahweh sent me! I brought Agag the king of
        Amalek, and the Amalekites I have utterly destroyed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The troops took from the plunder, sheep and cattle, the best of the
        things devoted to destruction, to sacrifice to Yahweh your God at Gilgal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Samuel said, \u201CIs there as much delight for Yahweh in burnt
        offerings and sacrifices as there is in obeying Yahweh? Look! To obey is
        better than sacrifice; to give heed than the fat of rams. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For rebellion is like the sin of divination; arrogance is like iniquity
        and idolatry. Because you have rejected the word of Yahweh, he has rejected
        you from being king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Saul said to Samuel, \u201CI have sinned because I have transgressed
        the commandment of Yahweh and your words, for I feared the troops and I listened
        to their voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So then, please pardon my sin and return with me so that I can worship
        Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Samuel said to Saul, \u201CI will not return with you, for you
        have rejected the word of Yahweh, and he has rejected you from being king
        over Israel!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'As Samuel turned around to go, he caught hold of the hem of his robe,
        and it tore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Samuel said to him, \u201CYahweh has torn the kingdom of Israel
        from you today and has given it to your neighbor who is better than you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Moreover, the Glory of Israel will not break faith and will not regret,
        for he is not a human that he should regret.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI have sinned! Now please honor me before the
        elders of my people and before Israel, and return with me so that I can worship
        Yahweh your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So Samuel returned after Saul, and Saul worshiped Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Samuel said, \u201CBring Agag the king of Amalek out to me!\u201D
        Agag came to him confidently, for Agag thought, \u201CSurely the bitterness
        of death is over.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Samuel said, \u201CJust as your sword bereaved women, so will your
        mother be bereaved among women!\u201D Then Samuel hacked Agag to pieces in
        the presence of Yahweh at Gilgal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Samuel went to Ramah and Saul went up to his house in Gibeah
        of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Samuel did not see Saul again until the day of his death, but Samuel
        mourned over Saul, and Yahweh regretted that he made Saul king over Israel. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Is Anointed'
      title: David Is Anointed
      number: 1
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Samuel, \u201CHow long will you mourn about Saul?
        I have rejected him from being king over Israel! Fill up your horn with oil
        and go. I will send you to Jesse the Bethlehemite, for I have chosen a king
        for myself among his sons.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Samuel said, \u201CHow can I go? If Saul hears, he will kill
        me.\u201D Yahweh said, \u201CYou must take a heifer from the herd with you,
        and you must say, \u2018I have come to sacrifice to Yahweh.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You will invite Jesse to the sacrifice and I will make known to you
        what you must do. You will anoint for me the one whom I tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Samuel did what Yahweh said. He came to Bethlehem, and the elders
        of the city came trembling to meet him. They said, \u201CHave you come in
        peace?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He said, \u201CI come in peace. I have come to sacrifice to Yahweh.
        Sanctify yourselves and come with me to the sacrifice.\u201D So he sanctified
        Jesse and his sons and invited them to the sacrifice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When they came, he saw Eliab and said, \u201CSurely his anointed
        one is before Yahweh!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Yahweh said to Samuel, \u201CDo not look at his appearance or
        at the height of his stature, because I have rejected him. For God does not
        see what man sees, for a man looks on the outward appearance, but Yahweh
        looks on the heart.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Jesse called Abinadab and made him pass before Samuel, and he
        said, \u201CThis one also Yahweh has not chosen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Jesse made Shammah pass before Samuel, but he said, \u201CYahweh
        also has not chosen this one.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Jesse made seven of his sons pass before Samuel, but Samuel said
        to Jesse, \u201CYahweh has not chosen any of these.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Samuel said to Jesse, \u201CAre all the young men here?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CThe youngest still remains, but look, he is shepherding
        the flock.\u201D And Samuel said to Jesse, \u201CSend and bring him, for
        we cannot sit down until he comes here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So he sent and brought him. Now he was ruddy with beautiful eyes
        and of handsome appearance. And Yahweh said, \u201CArise, anoint him, for
        this is he.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Saul in Torment'
      title: Saul in Torment
      number: 13
      content: 'So Samuel took the horn of oil and anointed him in the midst of his
        brothers. Then the Spirit of Yahweh rushed upon David from that day on. Then
        Samuel got up and went to Ramah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the Spirit of Yahweh departed from Saul and an evil spirit from
        Yahweh tormented him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So the servants of Saul said to him, \u201CLook please, an evil spirit
        from God is tormenting you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Please, let our lord command your servants who are before you! Let
        them seek a man skilled in playing on the lyre. When the evil spirit from
        God is upon you, he can play on it and you will feel better.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Saul said to his servants, \u201CPlease select a man who plays
        a stringed instrument well and bring him to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "One of the servants answered and said, \u201CLook, I have seen a
        son of Jesse the Bethlehemite who is skillful in playing a stringed instrument,
        a brave man, a warrior, prudent in speech, and handsome. And Yahweh is with
        him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So Saul sent messengers to Jesse and said, \u201CSend me David your
        son who is with the sheep.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Jesse took a donkey loaded with bread and a skin of wine and
        one young goat and sent them to Saul by the hand of David his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So David came to Saul and entered his service. He loved him greatly
        and he became Saul\u2019s armor bearer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Saul sent word to Jesse, saying, \u201CPlease let David stand
        before me, because he has found favor in my sight.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So whenever the evil spirit from God came to Saul, David would take
        the stringed instrument and play it with his hand. Then it would bring relief
        for Saul; he would feel better and the evil spirit would depart from him. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Philistine Champion Taunts Israel'
      title: The Philistine Champion Taunts Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'The Philistines gathered their camps for battle and they were gathered
        at Socoh which belongs to Judah. They camped between Socoh and Azekah in
        Ephes Dammim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Saul and the men of Israel were gathered and encamped in the
        valley of Elah, and they formed ranks for the battle to meet the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Philistines were standing on the hill on one side and the army
        of Israel was standing on the hill on the other side with the valley between
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then a champion went out from the camps of the Philistines, whose
        name was Goliath from Gath. His height was six cubits and a span.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A bronze helmet was on his head, and he was clothed with scale body
        armor; the weight of the body armor was five thousand bronze shekels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Bronze greaves were on his legs, and a bronze javelin was slung between
        his shoulders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The shaft of his spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam and the point
        of his spear weighed six hundred iron shekels. His shield bearer was walking
        in front of him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "He stood and called to the battle lines of Israel and said to them,
        \u201CWhy have you come out to form ranks for battle? Am I not the Philistine,
        and you the servants of Saul? Commission for yourselves a man and let him
        come down to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If he is able to fight with me and he defeats me, then we will be
        your servants; but if I prevail over him and defeat him, then you will be
        our servants and you will serve us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the Philistine said, \u201CI hereby defy the battle lines of
        Israel today! Give me a man so that we may fight each other!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: David Enters the Scene of Battle'
      title: David Enters the Scene of Battle
      number: 11
      content: 'When Saul and all Israel heard these words of the Philistine, they
        were dismayed and very afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now David was the son of an Ephrathite. This man was from Bethlehem
        of Judah, and his name was Jesse. He had eight sons; in the days of Saul
        this man was old, yet he still walked among the men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The three oldest sons of Jesse had gone and followed Saul to the
        battle. The names of his three sons who went to the battle were Eliab the
        firstborn, his second oldest was Abinadab, and the third was Shammah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now David was the youngest. The three oldest followed Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'but David went back and forth from Saul to feed the sheep of his
        father in Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now the Philistine came forward early and late, and he took his stand
        for forty days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jesse said to his son David, \u201CPlease take for your brothers
        an ephah of this roasted grain and these ten loaves of bread, and bring them
        quickly to the camp for your brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And these ten portions of cheese you will bring to the commander
        of the thousand; find out how your brothers are doing, and take their pledge.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now Saul and they and all the men of Israel were in the valley of
        Elah fighting the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'David rose early in the morning and left the sheep with a keeper,
        and he took the provisions and went as Jesse had commanded him. He came to
        the encampment while the troops were going to the battle line, and they raised
        the war cry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Israel and the Philistines drew up in battle lines, one battle line
        against the other.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'David left the baggage he had with him in the care of the baggage
        keeper, ran to the battle line, and came and asked how his brothers were
        doing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'While he was speaking to them, the champion, whose name was Goliath
        the Philistine from Gath, was coming up from the caves of the Philistines.
        He spoke just as he had previously, and David heard his words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When all the men of Israel saw the man, they fled from his presence
        and were very afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And the men of Israel said, \u201CDid you see this man who has come
        up? For he is going up to defy Israel! It will be that the man who defeats
        him, the king will make him very rich with great wealth and will give him
        his daughter in marriage and will make his father\u2019s house free in Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Now David had spoken to the men who were standing with him, saying,
        \u201CWhat will be done for the man who defeats this Philistine and removes
        the disgrace from Israel? For who is this uncircumcised Philistine that he
        defies the battle lines of the living God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And the troops had spoken to him according to this word, saying,
        \u201CSo it will be done for the man who defeats him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "His oldest brother Eliab heard while he was speaking to the men,
        and Eliab became very angry against David and said, \u201CWhy have you come
        down today, and with whom have you left those few sheep in the wilderness?
        I know your presumptuousness and the evil of your heart! For you have come
        down in order to see the battle!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "David replied, \u201CWhat have I done now? I merely asked a question!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: David Appears before Saul'
      title: David Appears before Saul
      number: 30
      content: 'He turned around from him to another opposite him and he spoke to
        him in the same way, and the people answered him as before.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now the words which David had spoken were heard and they reported
        them to Saul, and he summoned him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "David said to Saul, \u201CDo not let anyone\u2019s heart fail concerning
        him! Your servant will go and fight with this Philistine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But Saul said to David, \u201CYou will not be able to go against
        this Philistine to fight with him, because you are only a boy, whereas he
        has been a man of war since his childhood!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And David said to Saul, \u201CYour servant has been a shepherd of
        the flock for his father. If the lion or the bear would come and carry off
        a sheep from the group, "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'I would go out after it and strike it down and rescue the sheep from
        its mouth. If it rose against me, I would grab it by its beard and strike
        it down and kill it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Your servant has struck down both the lion and the bear, and this
        uncircumcised Philistine will be like one of them, because he defied the
        battle lines of the living God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And David said, \u201CYahweh, who rescued me from the hand of the
        lion and from the hand of the bear, will rescue me from the hand of this
        Philistine!\u201D Then Saul said to David, \u201CGo and may Yahweh be with
        you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then Saul clothed David with his own fighting attire and put a helmet
        of bronze on his head and clothed him with body armor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then David strapped on his sword over his fighting attire, but he
        tried in vain to walk around, for he was not trained to use them. So David
        said to Saul, \u201CI am not able to walk with these, because I am not trained
        to use them.\u201D So David removed them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then he took his staff in his hand, picked out for himself five smooth
        stones from the wadi, and he put them in his shepherd\u2019s bag, in the
        pouch. And with his sling in his hand, he approached the Philistine. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then the Philistine came on, getting nearer and nearer to David,
        with his shield bearer in front of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'When the Philistine looked and saw David, he despised him, for he
        was only a boy and ruddy with a handsome appearance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "So the Philistine said to David, \u201CAm I a dog, that you are coming
        to me with sticks?\u201D Then the Philistine cursed David by his gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "The Philistine said to David, \u201CCome to me so that I can give
        your flesh to the birds of heaven and to the wild animals of the field!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Then David said to the Philistine, \u201CYou are coming to me with
        a sword and with a spear and with a javelin, but I am coming to you in the
        name of Yahweh of hosts, the God of the battle lines of Israel, whom you
        have defied! "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'This day Yahweh will deliver you into my hand, and I will strike
        you down and cut off your head! Then I will give the corpses of the army
        of the Philistines this day to the birds of heaven and to the animals of
        the earth, so that all the earth may know that there is a God who is for
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: David Defeats Goliath'
      title: David Defeats Goliath
      number: 47
      content: "And all of this assembly will know that Yahweh does not rescue with
        sword or with spear, for the battle belongs to Yahweh, and he will give you
        into our hands!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'When the Philistine got up and came and drew near to meet David,
        David ran quickly to the battle line to meet the Philistine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Then David put his hand into the bag and took a stone from it and
        slung it. He struck the Philistine on his forehead, and the stone sank into
        his forehead, and he fell on his face to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "So David prevailed over the Philistine with the sling and with the
        stone, and he struck down the Philistine and killed him, but there was no
        sword in David\u2019s hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Then David ran and stood over the Philistine and took his sword and
        drew it from its sheath and killed him and cut off his head with it. When
        the Philistines saw that their champion was dead, they fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'The men of Israel and Judah got up, raised the war cry, and pursued
        the Philistines as far as the valley and up to the gates of Ekron. So the
        slain of the Philistines fell on the way to Shaaraim up to Gath and as far
        as Ekron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Then the Israelites returned from pursuing the Philistines and plundered
        their camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'And David took the head of the Philistine and brought it to Jerusalem
        and placed his weapons in his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "Now when Saul saw David going out to meet the Philistine, he said
        to Abner, the commander of the army, \u201CWhose son is this young man, Abner?\u201D
        And Abner said, \u201CAs your soul lives, O king, I do not know.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CYou inquire whose son this young man is.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'So when David returned from striking down the Philistine, Abner took
        him and brought him before Saul. The head of the Philistine was in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Then Saul said to him, \u201CWhose son are you, young man?\u201D
        And David said, \u201CI am the son of your servant Jesse the Bethlehemite.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Friendship of David and Jonathan'
      title: The Friendship of David and Jonathan
      number: 1
      content: 'When he finished speaking to Saul, the soul of Jonathan became attached
        to the soul of David, and Jonathan loved him as his own soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Saul took him on that very day and did not allow him to return to
        his father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jonathan made a covenant with David, because he loved him as
        his own soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: David\u2019s Successes Arouse Saul\u2019s Suspicions"
      title: "David\u2019s Successes Arouse Saul\u2019s Suspicions"
      number: 4
      content: 'Jonathan stripped off the robe that he was wearing and gave it to
        David, along with his fighting attire, and even his sword, his bow, and his
        belt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'David went out whenever Saul sent him, and he succeeded. So Saul
        appointed him over the men of the war, and it pleased all the people and
        even pleased the servants of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When they were coming back after David had returned from striking
        down the Philistine, the women went out from all the cities of Israel singing
        and dancing to meet King Saul with tambourines, with joy, and with three-stringed
        instruments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the women sang as they danced, and they said, \u201CSaul has
        struck down his thousands, but David his ten thousands!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Saul became very angry, and this saying displeased him, and he thought,
        \u201CThey have attributed to David ten thousands, but to me they have attributed
        thousands! What more can he have but the kingdom?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Saul was watching David with suspicion from that day onward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "On the next day, the evil spirit from God rushed upon Saul, and he
        prophesied in the middle of the house. Now David was playing the lyre with
        his hand on that day as usual, and the spear was in Saul\u2019s hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Saul hurled the spear and thought, \u201CI will pin David to
        the wall.\u201D But David eluded him twice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now Saul was threatened by the presence of David because Yahweh was
        with him, but had departed from Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Saul removed him from his presence, and made him commander of
        a thousand, so he marched in and out at the front of the army.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And David was achieving success in all his ways and Yahweh was with
        him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'but when Saul saw that he was very successful, he was severely threatened
        by him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "16: David Marries Saul\u2019s Daughter Michal"
      title: "David Marries Saul\u2019s Daughter Michal"
      number: 16
      content: 'However, all of Israel and Judah were loving David, for he was going
        forth and marching ahead of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul said to David, \u201CHere is my older daughter Merab. I
        will give her to you as your wife. Only be a brave warrior for me and fight
        the battles of Yahweh.\u201D For Saul thought, \u201CMy hand will not be
        against him, but let the hand of the Philistines be against him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But David said to Saul, \u201CWho am I, and who are my relatives,
        the clan of my father in Israel, that I should be a son-in-law to the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But at the time Saul\u2019s daughter Merab was to be given to David,
        she was given instead to Adriel the Meholathite as wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now Saul\u2019s daughter Michal loved David, so they told Saul, and
        the matter pleased him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Saul thought, \u201CI will give her to him, so that she may be
        a snare for him and the hand of the Philistines may be against him.\u201D
        So Saul said to David, \u201CFor a second time you can become my son-in-law
        today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Saul commanded his servants, \u201CSpeak to David in secret,
        saying, \u2018Look, the king is pleased with you, and all his servants love
        you. So then, become a son-in-law of the king.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Saul\u2019s servants spoke these words to David privately. But
        David said, \u201CIs it insignificant in your sight to become the son-in-law
        of the king, as I am a poor and lightly esteemed man?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So the servants of Saul informed him, saying, \u201CThis is what
        David said.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CThis is what you must say to David: \u2018The
        king desires no bride price except for a hundred foreskins of the Philistines,
        to avenge himself on the enemies of the king.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D (Now Saul
        had planned to allow David to fall by the hand of the Philistines.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So his servants told David these words, and the matter pleased David
        to become the son-in-law of the king as the specified time had not expired.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And David got up, and he and his men went and struck down two hundred
        men of the Philistines. Then David brought their foreskins, and they presented
        the full number to become the king\u2019s son-in-law. Then Saul gave him
        Michal his daughter as his wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When Saul realized that Yahweh was with David and his own daughter
        Michal loved him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Saul was threatened by David still more, so Saul became a perpetual
        enemy of David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the commanders of the Philistines went out for battle, and as
        often as they went out, David succeeded more than all the servants of Saul,
        and his name became very esteemed. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jonathan Intercedes for David'
      title: Jonathan Intercedes for David
      number: 1
      content: "Now Saul spoke to Jonathan his son and to all his servants about
        killing David, but Saul\u2019s son Jonathan liked David very much.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Jonathan informed David, saying, \u201CMy father Saul is trying
        to kill you; now please take care! In the morning you should stay in the
        hiding place and conceal yourself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I will go out and stand at my father\u2019s side in the field where
        you are, and I will speak about you to my father; if I find out anything
        I will tell it to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Jonathan spoke well about David to his father Saul and said to
        him, \u201CThe king should not sin against his servant David, because he
        has not sinned against you, and because his service for you has been very
        good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He put his life in his hand and attacked the Philistine, and Yahweh
        brought about a great victory for all of Israel, and you saw it and rejoiced!
        Now why should you sin against innocent blood by killing David without cause?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Saul listened to the voice of Jonathan and swore, \u201CAs Yahweh
        lives, he will not be put to death!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: David Has to Flee Again'
      title: David Has to Flee Again
      number: 7
      content: 'Jonathan called to David and told him all of these words. Then Jonathan
        brought David to Saul and he was before him as formerly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'War came again, so David went out and fought against the Philistines
        and defeated them thoroughly so that they fled before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the evil spirit from Yahweh came upon Saul while he was sitting
        in his house with his spear in his hand. And David was playing a stringed
        instrument in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Saul tried to pin David to the wall with the spear, but he eluded
        Saul, so that he struck the spear into the wall, and David fled and escaped
        that same night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Saul sent messengers to David\u2019s house to guard him and
        to kill him in the morning, but Michal his wife told David, saying, \u201CIf
        you do not save your life tonight, then tomorrow you will be killed!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Michal lowered David through the window, and he went and fled
        and escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Michal took the household god and put it on the bed and put
        a quilt of goat\u2019s hair at its head and covered it with the clothes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Saul sent messengers to arrest David, but she said, \u201CHe
        is ill.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So Saul sent the messengers to see David, saying, \u201CBring him
        up to me in the bed, so that I can kill him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the messengers came, to their surprise the idol was on the bed
        with the quilt of goat\u2019s hair at the head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul said to Michal, \u201CWhy have you deceived me like this
        and sent away my enemy, so that he escaped?\u201D Michal said to Saul, \u201CHe
        said to me, \u2018Let me go, why should I kill you?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So David fled and escaped, and he came to Samuel at Ramah and told
        him all that Saul had done to him. Then he and Samuel went and stayed in
        Naioth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And it was told to Saul, \u201CDavid is in Naioth in Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So Saul sent messengers to capture David. When they saw the company
        of the prophets prophesying and Samuel standing as chief over them, then
        the Spirit of God came upon Saul\u2019s messengers, and they also prophesied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So they told Saul, and he sent other messengers, and they also prophesied.
        Again Saul sent messengers a third time, and they also prophesied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then he also went to Ramah. When he came to the great cistern which
        was in Secu, he asked and said, \u201CWhere are Samuel and David?\u201D Someone
        said, \u201CLook they are in Naioth in Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So he went there to Naioth in Ramah and the Spirit of God came upon
        him also, and he walked along prophesying until he came to Naioth in Ramah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He also stripped off his clothes and prophesied before Samuel. He
        lay naked all that day and all night. Therefore they say, \u201CIs Saul also
        among the prophets?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jonathan Supports David over Saul'
      title: Jonathan Supports David over Saul
      number: 1
      content: "Then David fled from Naioth in Ramah and came and said before Jonathan,
        \u201CWhat have I done? What is my guilt and what is my sin before your father
        that he is trying to kill me?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CFar from it! You will not die! Look, my
        father does not do anything large or small unless he reveals it to me. Why
        should my father hide this thing or anything from me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then David took an oath again and said, \u201CYour father knows very
        well that I have found favor in your eyes, and he thought, \u2018Do not let
        Jonathan know this, lest he worry.\u2019 But as Yahweh lives and as your
        soul lives, surely there is merely a step between me and death!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David, \u201CWhatever you wish, I will do for
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "David said to Jonathan, \u201CLook, tomorrow is the new moon, and
        I should certainly sit with the king to eat. You must send me away so that
        I can hide myself in the field until the third evening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "If your father misses me at all, then you must say, \u2018David earnestly
        asked from me to run to Bethlehem his city, for the yearly sacrifice is there
        for all the clan.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If he says \u2018Good,\u2019 it will mean peace for your servant;
        but if he is very angry, know that he has decided to do me harm.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So you must show loyal love to your servant, for you have brought
        your servant into a covenant of Yahweh with you. But if there is guilt in
        me, then kill me yourself! But why should you bring me to your father?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Jonathan said, \u201CFar be it from you! For if I know for certain
        that my father decided evil should come upon you, would I not have told it
        to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David said to Jonathan, \u201CWho will tell me if what your
        father answers you is harsh?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Jonathan said to David, \u201CCome, let us go out to the field.\u201D
        So the two of them went out to the field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David, \u201CYahweh the God of Israel is my
        witness that I will question my father by this time the day after tomorrow.
        And look, if he is well disposed toward you, will I not send word to you
        and disclose it to you?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So may Yahweh punish Jonathan and more if my father decides to do
        you harm and if I fail to disclose it to you and send word to you that you
        can go safely. And may Yahweh be with you, as he has been with my father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And not while I am still alive, will you not show the loyal love
        of Yahweh with me, that I may not die?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And do not cut off your loyal love from my family forever, not even
        when Yahweh exterminates each of the enemies of David from the face of the
        earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Jonathan made a covenant with the house of David, saying, \u201CMay
        Yahweh call the enemies of David to account.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Jonathan again made David swear an oath, because he loved him;
        for with the love of his soul he loved him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jonathan said to him, \u201CTomorrow is the new moon, and you
        will be missed, for your seat will stay empty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'On the third day you must go down quickly and go to the place where
        you hid yourself on the day all this started and remain beside the stone
        Ezel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will shoot three arrows to the side as if I were shooting at a
        target. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then I will send word to my servant, \u2018Go, find the arrows!\u2019
        If I clearly say to the boy, \u2018Look, the arrows are on this side of you;
        bring it,\u2019 then come, for it means peace for you. And there is no problem,
        as Yahweh lives.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But if I say this to the young man, \u2018Look, the arrows are beyond
        you,\u2019 go, for Yahweh has sent you away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And as for the matter about which you and I spoke, look, Yahweh is
        between you and me forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So David hid himself in the field. When the new moon came, the king
        was seated at the feast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The king sat at his seat as before, the seat by the wall, and Jonathan
        got up, and Abner sat beside Saul, but David\u2019s place was empty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Saul said nothing on that day, for he thought, \u201CSomething
        happened to him. He is not ceremonially clean; surely he is not clean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And then on the next day, the second day of the new moon, that David\u2019s
        place was empty. So Saul asked Jonathan his son, \u201CWhy did the son of
        Jesse not come either yesterday or today to the feast?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jonathan answered Saul, \u201CDavid earnestly asked permission from
        me to go up to Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "He said, \u2018Send me away, please, for our clan sacrifice is in
        the city, and my brother commanded me to be present. So then, if I have found
        favor in your eyes, please let me slip away and see my brothers.\u2019 Therefore
        he has not come to the table of the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Saul became angry at Jonathan and said to him, \u201CYou son
        of a perverse, rebellious woman! Do I not know that you have chosen the son
        of Jesse to your shame and to the shame of your mother\u2019s nakedness? "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "For as long as the son of Jesse is alive on the earth, you and your
        kingdom will not be established! So then, send and bring him to me, for he
        will surely die!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But Jonathan answered his father Saul and said to him, \u201CWhy
        should he be put to death? What has he done?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then Saul hurled his spear at him to kill him. So Jonathan knew that
        his father had decided to kill David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Jonathan got up from the table enraged, and did not eat on the second
        day of the new moon because he was upset about David, because his father
        had disgraced him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And then in the morning Jonathan went out to the field for the appointment
        with David, and a young boy was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "He said to his servant, \u201CRun, please find the arrows that I
        am shooting!\u201D The boy ran, and he shot the arrow to pass over him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "When the boy came up to the place of the arrow that Jonathan had
        shot, Jonathan called out after the boy and said, \u201CIs not the arrow
        beyond you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then Jonathan called out after the boy, \u201CQuick, hurry, do not
        linger!\u201D And Jonathan\u2019s servant collected the arrows and came to
        his master. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But the boy did not know anything about this; only Jonathan and David
        knew the matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Jonathan gave his weapons to his servant and said to him, \u201CGo,
        bring them to the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The boy left, and then David got up from the south side, and he fell
        on his face to the ground and bowed three times. And they kissed each other
        and wept together, but David wept the most. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Jonathan said to David, \u201CGo in peace, because we have sworn,
        the two of us, an oath in the name of Yahweh, saying, \u201CYahweh will be
        between me and you, and between my offspring and your offspring forever.\u201D
        Then he got up and left, and Jonathan went into the city. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Encounters the Priests of Nob'
      title: David Encounters the Priests of Nob
      number: 1
      content: "Now David came to Nob, to Ahimelech the priest. And Ahimelech came
        trembling to meet David, and he said to him, \u201CWhy are you alone and
        there are no men with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So David said to Ahimelech the priest, \u201CThe king charged me
        with a matter and said to me, \u2018No one must know anything about this
        matter on which I am sending you, with which I have charged you and the servants.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        So I have arranged to meet with my servants at a certain place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now then, what do you have at hand? Give me five loaves of bread
        or whatever is here.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The priest answered David and said, \u201CThere is no ordinary bread
        here at hand; there is only holy bread, but only if the young men have kept
        themselves from women.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "David answered the priest and said to him, \u201CIndeed, women were
        held back from us as it has been when I\u2019ve gone out before. And the
        things of the young men are holy when it is an ordinary journey. How much
        more today will the things be holy?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the priest gave him the holy bread, for there was no bread there
        except the bread of the Presence, which was removed from before Yahweh, in
        order to set hot bread there on the day when it was taken away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now there was a man from the servants of Saul on that day, detained
        before Yahweh, whose name was Doeg the Edomite, the chief of Saul\u2019s
        shepherds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "David asked Ahimelech, \u201CIs there not at your disposal a spear
        or a sword? For I took neither my sword nor my weapons with me because the
        king\u2019s matter was urgent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: David Flees to Achish in Gath'
      title: David Flees to Achish in Gath
      number: 9
      content: "So the priest said, \u201CThe sword of Goliath the Philistine whom
        you killed in the valley of Elah is here, wrapped in a cloth behind the ephod.
        If you want to take it for yourself, then take it, for there is no other
        except it here.\u201D And David said, \u201CThere is none like it; give it
        to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So David got up and fled on that day from the presence of Saul, and
        he came to Achish the king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The servants of Achish said to him, \u201CIs not this David the king
        of the land? Is it not for this one that they sang in the dances, saying,
        \u2018Saul killed his thousands, but David his ten thousands?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'David took these words seriously and felt severely threatened by
        Achish the king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So he changed his behavior before them and pretended to be mad in
        their presence. He made scratches on the doors of the gate and let his saliva
        run down into his beard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Achish said to his servants, \u201CLook, you see a madman! Why
        did you bring him to me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Do I lack madmen that you have brought this one to act like a madman
        before me? Should this one enter my household?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Takes Revenge on the Priests Who Helped David'
      title: Saul Takes Revenge on the Priests Who Helped David
      number: 1
      content: "David went from there and escaped to the cave of Adullam. When his
        brothers and all his father\u2019s household heard, they came down to him
        there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Every man in distress and every man who had a creditor and every
        embittered man gathered to him, and he became their commander. Now there
        were about four hundred men with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And David went up from there to Mizpah of Moab. He said to the king
        of Moab, \u201CPlease let my father and my mother stay with you until I know
        what God will do for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So he brought them before the king of Moab, and they stayed with
        him all the days David was in the stronghold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Gad the prophet said to David, \u201CYou should not stay in
        the stronghold; leave and go into the land of Judah.\u201D So David left
        and came to the forest of Hereth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now Saul heard that David and the men who were with him had been
        located. Saul was sitting at Gibeah under the tamarisk tree at Ramah. Now
        his spear was in his hand and all his servants were stationed around him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Saul said to the servants who were standing around him, \u201CPlease
        listen, Benjaminites! Will the son of Jesse give you all fields and vineyards?
        Will he make all of you commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For all of you have conspired against me, and no one discloses to
        me the making of an agreement between my son and the son of Jesse! None of
        you have had sympathy for me or disclosed to me that my son commissioned
        my servant against me to ambush me as has been done this day!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Doeg the Edomite, who was stationed among the servants of Saul,
        answered and said, \u201CI saw the son of Jesse going to Nob, to Ahimelech
        the son of Ahitub. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he inquired of Yahweh for him and gave him provisions and gave
        him the sword of Goliath the Philistine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the king sent to summon Ahimelech the son of Ahitub the priest,
        and all his father\u2019s household, the priests who were at Nob. So all
        of them came to the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Saul said, \u201CListen please, son of Ahitub.\u201D He said, \u201CHere
        I am, my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Saul said to him, \u201CWhy did you conspire against me, you
        and the son of Jesse, when you gave to him bread and a sword, and by inquiring
        of God for him so that he might arise against me to ambush me as has been
        done this day?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Ahimelech answered the king and said, \u201CAnd who among all
        your servants is as faithful as David? He is the son-in-law of the king who
        moves quickly to safeguard you and is honored in your house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Only today I began to inquire of God for him. Far be it from me that
        the king should impute anything against his servant or against my father\u2019s
        household, for your servant has not known any of this matter, little or much.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CYou must certainly die, Ahimelech, you
        and all your father\u2019s household!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So the king said to the runners who were stationed around him, \u201CTurn
        and kill the priests of Yahweh, because they also support David and because
        they knew that he was fleeing and did not disclose it to me.\u201D But the
        servants of the king were not willing to raise their hand to attack the priests
        of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the king said to Doeg, \u201CYou turn and attack the priests!\u201D
        So Doeg the Edomite turned and attacked the priests himself, and on that
        day he killed eighty-five men who wore the linen ephod. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he put to the sword Nob, the city of the priests, from man to
        woman, from child to infant, and ox and donkey and sheep; all to the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But, one of the sons of Ahimelech the son of Ahitub, whose name was
        Abiathar, escaped and fled after David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Abiathar told David that Saul had killed the priests of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then David said to Abiathar, \u201CI knew on that day that Doeg the
        Edomite was there, that he would certainly tell Saul. I am responsible for
        the deaths of all your father\u2019s household!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Stay with me! Do not fear, because he who seeks my life seeks your
        life. You are in good care with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Defeats the Philistines at Keilah'
      title: David Defeats the Philistines at Keilah
      number: 1
      content: "Now they told David, \u201CLook, the Philistines are fighting in
        Keilah and they are raiding the threshing floors.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So David inquired of Yahweh, saying, \u201CShall I go and attack
        these Philistines?\u201D And Yahweh said to David, \u201CGo and attack the
        Philistines and save Keilah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But David\u2019s men said to him, \u201CLook, we are afraid here
        in Judah. How much more if we go to Keilah to the battle lines of the Philistines?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So David again inquired of Yahweh, and Yahweh answered him and said,
        \u201CGet up, go down to Keilah, for I am giving the Philistines into your
        hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: David Flees from Saul at Keilah'
      title: David Flees from Saul at Keilah
      number: 5
      content: 'So David and his men went to Keilah and fought with the Philistines.
        They drove off their livestock and dealt them a heavy blow. So David saved
        the inhabitants of Keilah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now when Abiathar the son of Ahimelech fled to David at Keilah, he
        went down with an ephod in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When it was told to Saul that David had gone to Keilah, Saul said,
        \u201CGod has given him into my hand, because he has shut himself in by going
        into a city with two barred gates.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Saul then summoned all of the army for the battle, to go down to
        Keilah to lay a siege against David and his men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When David learned that Saul was plotting evil against him, he said
        to Abiathar the priest, \u201CBring the ephod here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And David said, \u201CO Yahweh, God of Israel, your servant has clearly
        heard that Saul is seeking to come to Keilah to destroy the city because
        of me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Will the rulers of Keilah deliver me into his hand? Will Saul come
        down as your servant has heard? O Yahweh, God of Israel, please tell your
        servant!\u201D And Yahweh said, \u201CHe will come down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then David said, \u201CWill the rulers of Keilah deliver me and my
        men into the hand of Saul?\u201D And Yahweh said, \u201CThey will deliver
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: David Eludes Saul\u2019s Pursuit"
      title: "David Eludes Saul\u2019s Pursuit"
      number: 13
      content: 'So David and his men got up, about six hundred men, and went out
        from Keilah and wandered wherever they could go. When it was told to Saul
        that David had escaped from Keilah, he stopped his pursuit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'David remained in the wilderness, in the strongholds, and in the
        hill country in the wilderness of Ziph. And Saul sought him continually,
        but God did not give him into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When David realized that Saul had gone out to seek his life, David
        was in the wilderness of Ziph at Horesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Jonathan the son of Saul got up and went to David at Horesh, and
        encouraged him through God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He said to him, \u201CDo not be afraid, for the hand of my father
        Saul will not find you. You will be king over Israel, and I will be second
        to you. My father Saul knows this also.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the two of them made a covenant before Yahweh. David remained
        at Horesh, and Jonathan went to his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Ziphites went up to Saul at Gibeah, saying, \u201CIs not
        David hiding among us in the strongholds at Horesh on the hill of Hakilah,
        which is south of Jeshimon? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So then, O king, whenever you want to come down, come down, and it
        will be for us to deliver him into the hand of the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Saul said to them, \u201CMay you be blessed by Yahweh, for you
        have shown me compassion! "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Go, please, make certain again! Find out and see exactly where he
        is and who has seen him there! For they have said to me, \u2018He is very
        cunning.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Look, find out all of the hiding places where he hides. Then return
        to me with dependable information, and I will go with you. And then if he
        is there in the land, then I will seek him among all the thousands of Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then they got up and went to Ziph before Saul. Now David and his
        men were in the wilderness of Maon in the Arabah, to the south of Jeshimon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Saul and his men went to seek him, and they told David, so he
        went down to the rock and stayed in the wilderness of Maon. When Saul heard
        this, he pursued David into the wilderness of Maon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Saul went on one side of the mountain, and David and his men went
        on the other side of the mountain. David was hurrying to get away from Saul,
        while Saul and his men were closing in on David and his men to capture them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But a messenger came to Saul, saying, \u201CHurry and come, because
        the Philistines have made a raid on the land!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Saul returned from pursuing David, and he went to confront the
        Philistines. Therefore, they called that place the Rock of Division.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: ' David went up from there and stayed in the strongholds of En Gedi. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Spares Saul in the Cave at En Gedi'
      title: David Spares Saul in the Cave at En Gedi
      number: 1
      content: "When Saul returned from pursuing the Philistines, they told him,
        \u201CLook, David is in the wilderness of En Gedi.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Saul took three thousand chosen men from all Israel, and he and
        his men went to search for David in the direction of the Rocks of the Mountain
        Goats.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He came to the sheep pens beside the road, and a cave was there.
        Then Saul went in to relieve himself. Now David and his men were sitting
        in the innermost part of the cave. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And David\u2019s men said to him, \u201CLook, today is the day about
        which Yahweh said to you, \u2018See, I am giving your enemy into your hand,
        and you can do to him whatever seems good to you.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D So David
        got up and secretly cut the hem of Saul\u2019s robe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And then afterward David felt guilty, because he had cut the hem
        of Saul\u2019s robe.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to his men, \u201CFar be it from me in Yahweh, that I do
        this thing to my lord, to Yahweh\u2019s anointed one, by stretching out my
        hand against him! For he is the anointed one of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So David rebuked his men with the words and did not allow them to
        rise against Saul. And Saul got up from the cave, and he went on his way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David got up afterward and went out of the cave and called after
        Saul, \u201CMy lord the king!\u201D When Saul looked after him, David knelt
        down with his face to the ground and bowed down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then David said to Saul, \u201CWhy do you listen to the words of
        people who say: \u2018Look, David is seeking to do you harm\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Look, this day your eyes have seen that Yahweh gave you today into
        my hand in the cave, and some said to kill you. But I took pity on you and
        said, \u2018I will not stretch out my hand against my lord, because he is
        Yahweh\u2019s anointed one.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now, my father, see, yes, see, the hem of your robe in my hand! For
        when I cut the hem of your robe I did not kill you. Know and realize that
        there is no evil or rebellion in my hand. I did not sin against you, but
        you are hunting down my life to take it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'May Yahweh judge between me and you, and may Yahweh avenge me on
        you, but my hand will not be against you! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Just as the ancient proverb says, \u2018From the wicked, wickedness
        goes out,\u2019 but my hand will not be against you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'After whom did the king of Israel go out? After whom are you pursuing?
        After a dead dog? After one flea? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "May Yahweh be the judge, and let him judge between me and you, and
        may he see and plead my case. May he vindicate me against you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When David finished speaking these words to Saul, Saul said, \u201CIs
        this your voice, my son David?\u201D And Saul lifted up his voice and wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he said to David, \u201CYou are more righteous than I, for you
        have repaid me the good, but I have repaid you the evil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You have explained to me today that you have dealt well with me,
        how Yahweh delivered me into your hand but you did not kill me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For a man has found his enemy but sent him on his way safely. Now
        may Yahweh reward you with good in return for this day, for what you have
        done for me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So now then, look, I know that you will certainly be king and the
        kingdom of Israel will be established in your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So then, swear to me by Yahweh that you will not cut off my descendants
        after me and that you will not wipe out my name from my father\u2019s house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So David swore this on oath to Saul, and Saul went to his house,
        but David and his men went up to the stronghold. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samuel\u2019s DeathDavid and Abigail"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s DeathDavid and Abigail"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Samuel died, and all Israel assembled and mourned for him. They
        buried him at his house at Ramah. Then David got up and went down to the
        wilderness of Paran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now there was a man in Maon, whose business was in Carmel. The man
        was very rich and owned three thousand sheep and a thousand goats. Now the
        shearing of his sheep was taking place in Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The name of the man was Nabal, and the name of his wife was Abigail.
        Now the woman was wise and beautiful, but the man was stubborn and mean,
        and he was as his heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David heard in the wilderness that Nabal was shearing his sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David sent ten young men, and David said to the young men, \u201CGo
        up to Carmel and go to Nabal; you will greet him in my name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then you must say to him, \u2018Long life to you, and may it go well
        with you, with your house, and with all that is yours.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now I have heard that you have shearers. Now while your shepherds
        were with us, we did not mistreat them, and nothing of theirs was missing,
        all the days they were in Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ask your servants and they will tell you! Let the young men find
        favor in your eyes because we have come on a feast day. Please give whatever
        you have on hand for your servants and for your son David.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So David\u2019s young men came and they spoke all these words to
        Nabal in the name of David. Then they waited. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Nabal answered David\u2019s servants and said, \u201CWho is David?
        And who is the son of Jesse? Today, there are many servants breaking away
        from the presence of their masters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Should I take my bread and my water and my meat which I have slaughtered
        for my shearers and give it to men whom I do not know where they are from? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So David\u2019s young men turned on their way and returned and came
        and told him according to all these words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then David said to his men, \u201CEach man strap on his sword!\u201D
        So each one strapped on his sword, and David also strapped on his sword.
        About four hundred men went up after David, while two hundred remained with
        the baggage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But a young man of the servants told Abigail, Nabal\u2019s wife,
        saying, \u201CLook, David sent messengers from the desert to greet our master,
        but he addressed them angrily, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'even though the men were very good to us; we were not mistreated
        and did not miss anything all the days we went about with them while we were
        in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They were a wall to us both night and day, all the days we were with
        them keeping the sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And so then, know and consider what you should do, for evil has been
        decided against our master and against all his household, and he is such
        a wicked man, nobody can reason with him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Abigail quickly took two hundred loaves of bread, two skins
        of wine, five prepared sheep, five seahs of roasted grain, a hundred raisin
        cakes, and two hundred fig cakes, and she put them on the donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then she said to her servants, \u201CGo ahead before me; look, I
        am coming after you,\u201D but she did not tell her husband Nabal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And then, as she was riding on the donkey and was going down the
        ravine of the mountain, David and his men were coming down to meet her, and
        she met them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now David had said, \u201CSurely in vain I guarded all that this
        fellow had in the desert. And nothing was missed of all that was his, but
        he returned evil against me in place of good! "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "May God severely punish the enemies of David and again do thus if
        I leave behind anything that is his until the morning, not even one male!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "When Abigail saw David, she hurried and got down from the donkey
        and fell on her face before David\u2019s anger, and she bowed down to the
        ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "She fell at his feet and said, \u201COn me, my lord, be the guilt!
        Please let your female servant speak to you personally! Hear the words of
        your female servant! "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Please do not let my lord set his heart against this worthless man,
        Nabal; for as his name, so is he. Nabal is his name, and stupidity is with
        him! But I, your female servant, did not see the young men of my lord whom
        you sent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So then, my lord, as Yahweh lives and as your soul lives, since Yahweh
        restrained you from bloodguilt by taking matters into your own hand, so then,
        may your enemies be like Nabal, even those who seek to do my lord harm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So then, this gift which your female servant has brought to my lord,
        may it be given to the young men who follow my lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Please forgive the transgression of your female servant, because
        Yahweh will certainly make a lasting house for my lord, because my lord is
        fighting the battles of Yahweh, and evil will not be found in you as long
        as you live.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Should a man arise to pursue you and to seek your life, may the life
        of my lord be wrapped in the pouch of the living with Yahweh your God. But
        as for the life of your enemy, he will sling it from within the pocket of
        the sling! '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And then when Yahweh has done for my lord according to all the good
        that he has spoken concerning you, and has appointed you as leader over Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "then this will not be an obstacle for you or a stumbling block of
        conscience for my lord either by the shedding of blood without cause or by
        my lord taking matters into his own hands. And when Yahweh does good to my
        lord, then remember your female servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then David said to Abigail, \u201CBlessed be Yahweh the God of Israel
        who has sent you this day to meet me! "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And blessed be your discretion, and blessed be you who have prevented
        me this day from bloodguilt and from delivering myself by my own hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But as Yahweh lives, the God of Israel who has prevented me from
        harming you, if you had not hurried and come to meet me, surely there would
        not have been one male left alive for Nabal by the light of morning!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then David took from her hand what she had brought for him, and he
        said to her, \u201CGo up to your house in peace. See, I have listened to
        your voice, and I have granted your request.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then Abigail went to Nabal, and look, he was holding a feast in his
        house like the feast of the king. Nabal was enjoying himself, and he was
        very drunk, so she did not tell him a thing, nothing at all, until the light
        of morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And then in the morning when the wine had gone out of Nabal, his
        wife told him these words. Then his heart died within him, and he became
        like a stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And then, about ten days later, Yahweh struck Nabal and he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "When David heard that Nabal had died, he said, \u201CBlessed be Yahweh
        who has vindicated the case of my reproach from the hand of Nabal, and he
        has kept back his servant from evil; but Yahweh has returned the evil of
        Nabal on his own head.\u201D Then David sent and spoke with Abigail to take
        her for his wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "So the servants of David came to Abigail at Carmel, and they spoke
        to her, saying, \u201CDavid has sent us to you to take you for his wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "She got up and bowed down with her face to the ground and said, \u201CHere
        is your female servant, as a slave to wash the feet of my lord\u2019s servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Then Abigail quickly got up and rode on the donkey, along with five
        of her maidservants who attended her, and she went after the messengers of
        David and became his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'David had also taken Ahinoam from Jezreel, and both of them became
        his wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "(Now Saul had given his daughter Michal, David\u2019s wife, to Palti
        the son of Laish, who was from Gallim.) "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Again Spares Saul'
      title: David Again Spares Saul
      number: 1
      content: "The Ziphites came to Saul at Gibeah, saying, \u201CIs not David hiding
        on the hill of Hakilah opposite Jeshimon?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Saul got up and went down to the wilderness of Ziph, and three
        thousand chosen men of Israel with him, to seek David in the wilderness of
        Ziph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Saul was on the hill of Hakilah, which is opposite Jeshimon by
        the road, but David was staying in the wilderness. When he realized that
        Saul had come to the wilderness after him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David sent spies, and he learned that Saul had come for certain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then David got up and came to the place where Saul had encamped,
        and David saw the place where Saul was lying down, as well as Abner the son
        of Ner, the commander of his army. (Now Saul was lying in the encampment,
        and the army was encamping around him.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "David answered and said to Ahimelech the Hittite and to Abishai the
        son of Zeruiah the brother of Joab, saying, \u201CWho will go down with me
        to Saul, in the camp?\u201D And Abishai said, \u201CI will go down with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So David and Abishai came to the army by night, and there was Saul
        lying asleep in the encampment with his spear thrust into the ground near
        his head, and Abner and the army were lying all around him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Abishai said to David, \u201CGod has handed over your enemy
        into your hand today! So then, please let me pin him to the ground with the
        spear one time, and I will not strike him twice.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But David said to Abishai, \u201CDo not destroy him! For who has
        stretched out his hand against Yahweh\u2019s anointed one and remained blameless?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And David said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, certainly Yahweh will strike
        him, or his day will come and he will die, or he will go down in the battle
        and perish.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Yahweh forbid me from stretching out my hand against Yahweh\u2019s
        anointed one! So then, please take the spear that is near his head and the
        jar of water, and let us go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So David took the spear and the jar of water from near Saul\u2019s
        head, and they went away. No one saw, no one knew, and no one awakened, for
        all of them were sleeping because a deep sleep of Yahweh had fallen upon
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then David went to the other side and stood on the top of the hill
        at a distance; the distance was great between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "David called out to the army and to Abner the son of Ner, \u201CWill
        you not answer, Abner?\u201D And Abner answered and said, \u201CWho are you
        that you call to the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So David said to Abner, \u201CAre you not a man? And who is like
        you in Israel? Why did you not keep watch over your lord the king? For one
        of the people came to destroy your lord the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This thing that you have done is not good. As Yahweh lives, surely
        you people deserve to die since you have not kept watch over your lord, over
        Yahweh\u2019s anointed one! So then, see where the king\u2019s spear is and
        the jar of water that was near his head!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul recognized David\u2019s voice and said, \u201CIs this your
        voice, my son David?\u201D And David said, \u201CIt is my voice, my lord
        the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWhy is my lord pursuing after his servant? For
        what have I done? And what evil is in my hand? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And so then, please let my lord the king listen to the words of his
        servant: If Yahweh has incited you against me, may he delight in an offering;
        but if it is mortals, may they be accursed before Yahweh, for they have driven
        me away today from sharing in the inheritance of Yahweh, saying, \u2018Go,
        serve other gods!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And so then, do not let my blood fall to the ground away from the
        presence of Yahweh, for the king of Israel has gone out to seek a single
        flea, as one hunts a partridge in the mountains.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CI have sinned! Come back, David my son, for
        I will not harm you again, because my life was precious in your eyes this
        day. Look, I have acted like a fool and have made a terrible mistake.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "David answered and said, \u201CHere is the king\u2019s spear; let
        one of the young men come over and take it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Yahweh repays to each one his righteousness and his faithfulness,
        for Yahweh gave you into my hand today, but I was not willing to stretch
        out my hand against Yahweh\u2019s anointed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Look, as your life was precious in my eyes this day, may my life
        be great in the eyes of Yahweh, and may he rescue me from all trouble.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Saul said to David, \u201CBlessed are you, my son David; you
        will not only do many things, but also will always succeed!\u201D Then David
        went on his way and Saul returned to his place. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Returns to Achish'
      title: David Returns to Achish
      number: 1
      content: "Then David thought to himself, \u201CNow I will perish one day by
        the hand of Saul! There is nothing better for me but that I must certainly
        escape to the land of the Philistines. Then Saul will desist from searching
        for me further in all of the territories of Israel, and so I will escape
        from his hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So David got up and crossed over, he and the six hundred men who
        were with him, to Achish the son of Maoch, the king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David settled with Achish in Gath, he and his men, each with his
        household. David took along his two wives Ahinoam from Jezreel and Abigail
        the wife of Nabal the Carmelite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And it was reported to Saul that David had fled to Gath, so he no
        longer searched for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then David said to Achish, \u201CPlease, if I have found favor in
        your eyes, then let them give me a place in one of the country towns that
        I can live there. Why should your servant live in the royal city with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Achish gave him Ziklag on that day. (Therefore, Ziklag has belonged
        to the kings of Judah until this day.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The number of days that David lived in the countryside of the Philistines
        was one year and four months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now David and his men went up and raided the Geshurites and the Girzites
        and the Amalekites, for they had been living in the land for a long time
        in the direction of Shur and as far as the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So David struck the land and did not leave a man or a woman alive;
        he took the sheep, the cattle, the donkeys, the camels, and the clothing.
        Then he returned and came to Achish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Achish said, \u201CAgainst whom have you raided today?\u201D
        David said, \u201CAgainst the Negev of Judah and against the Negev of the
        Jerahmeelites and against the Negev of the Kenites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And David did not leave alive a man or a woman to bring them back
        to Gath, thinking, \u201CSo that they will not report about us, saying, \u2018David
        did thus and so.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D Thus was his practice all the days that
        he lived in the countryside of the Philistines. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Achish trusted David, saying, \u201CHe has made himself utterly
        hated among his people in Israel, and he will be my servant forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " Now in those days the Philistines gathered their forces for war
        to fight against Israel. So Achish said to David, \u201CCertainly you realize
        that you must go out with me in the army, you and your men.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Saul Inquires of the Medium at Endor'
      title: Saul Inquires of the Medium at Endor
      number: 2
      content: "David said to Achish, \u201CVery well, you will know what your servant
        can do.\u201D Achish said to David, \u201CVery well, I will make you my bodyguard
        for life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '(Now Samuel had died, and all Israel had mourned for him, and they
        had buried him in Ramah, his own city. And Saul had expelled the mediums
        and the soothsayers from the land.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the Philistines assembled and came and encamped at Shunem, so
        Saul assembled all Israel, and they encamped at Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Saul saw the army of the Philistines, he was afraid and his
        heart trembled greatly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Saul inquired of Yahweh, but Yahweh did not answer him, not by
        dreams or by the Urim or by the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Saul said to his servants, \u201CSearch for me a woman who is
        a medium so that I may go to her and inquire of her.\u201D His servants said
        to him, \u201CLook there is a woman who is a medium in Endor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Saul disguised himself and put on other clothes, and he went with
        two of his men. And they came to the woman by night and he said, \u201CPlease
        consult a spirit for me through the ritual pit, and bring up for me the one
        whom I tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the woman said to him, \u201CLook, you know what Saul did, how
        he exterminated the mediums and the soothsayers from the land! Why are you
        setting a trap for my life to kill me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Saul swore to her by Yahweh, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, you will
        not be punished for this thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the woman asked, \u201CWhom shall I bring up for you?\u201D He
        said, \u201CBring up Samuel for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When the woman saw Samuel, she cried out with a loud voice, and the
        woman said to Saul, \u201CWhy did you deceive me? You are Saul!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The king said to her, \u201CDo not be afraid! What do you see?\u201D
        And the woman said to Saul, \u201CI see a god coming up from the ground!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said to her, \u201CWhat is his appearance?\u201D She said,
        \u201CAn old man is coming up, and he is wrapped in a robe.\u201D Then Saul
        realized that it was Samuel, and he knelt with his face to the ground and
        bowed down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201CWhy have you disturbed me by bringing
        me up?\u201D And Saul said, \u201CI am in distress! For the Philistines are
        about to make war against me, but God has turned away from me, and he does
        not answer me any more, not by the prophets or by the dreams. So I called
        to you to let me know what I should do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Samuel said, \u201CWhy do you ask me, since Yahweh has turned
        away from you and has become your enemy? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yahweh has done to you just as he spoke by my hand! Yahweh has torn
        the kingdom from your hand and has given it to your neighbor, to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Because you did not obey Yahweh and did not carry out the fierce
        anger of his wrath against Amalek, therefore Yahweh has done this thing to
        you today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Yahweh will also give Israel with you into the hands of the Philistines,
        and tomorrow you and your sons will be with me, and Yahweh will also give
        the army of Israel into the hand of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Saul immediately fell prostrate to the ground, and he was very
        afraid because of the words of Samuel; there was no more strength in him,
        for he had not eaten food all day and all night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the woman came to Saul and realized that he was absolutely terrified,
        so she said to him, \u201CLook, your female servant has obeyed you, and I
        have risked my life. I have listened to your words that you have spoken to
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So then, you also please listen to the voice of your female servant,
        and let me set before you a morsel of bread, and you eat so that you will
        have strength in you when you go on your way.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But he refused and said, \u201CI will not eat!\u201D However, his
        servants urged him, and the woman also. So he listened to what they said,
        and he got up from the ground and sat on the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now the woman had a fattened bull calf in the house, so she quickly
        slaughtered it and took flour, kneaded dough, and baked him some unleavened
        bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'She brought it before Saul and his servants, and they ate. Then they
        got up and went away that very night. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Leaves the Service of Achish'
      title: David Leaves the Service of Achish
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the Philistines assembled all their forces at Aphek, and Israel
        was encamped at the spring that is in Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The rulers of the Philistines were passing on according to hundreds
        and thousands, David and his men passing on at the rear with Achish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the commanders of the Philistines said, \u201CWhat are these
        Hebrews doing here?\u201D And Achish said to the commanders of the Philistines,
        \u201CIs this not David, the servant of Saul, the king of Israel, who has
        been with me for days and years? I have not found anything threatening in
        him from the day of his desertion until this day!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the commanders of the Philistines were angry with him and they
        said to him, \u201CSend the man back so that he might return to his place
        where you have assigned him! But he will not go down with us into the battle,
        so that he does not become an adversary to us in the battle. By what could
        this fellow make himself favorable to his lord? Is it not with the heads
        of these men? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Is this not David about whom they sing in the dances, saying, \u2018Saul
        has killed his thousands, but David his ten thousands\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Achish called David and said to him, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, certainly
        you were honest, and I am pleased to have you marching with me in the campaign.
        For I have not found any wrong in you from the day you came to me until this
        day, but in the eyes of the rulers, you are not good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So then, return and go in peace, so that you do not do something
        that displeases the rulers of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David said to Achish, \u201CBut what have I done? And what have
        you found in your servant from the day that I entered your service until
        this day, that I should not go and fight against the enemies of my lord the
        king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Achish answered and said to David, \u201CI know that you are
        good in my eyes, like an angel of God! However, the commanders of the Philistines
        have said, \u2018He must not go up with us into the battle.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So then, rise early in the morning, you and the servants of your
        lord who came with you. When you rise early in the morning and it is light
        enough for you, leave. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So David set out early, he and his men, to leave in the morning to
        return to the land of the Philistines, but the Philistines went up to Jezreel. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Recovers His Loved Ones'
      title: David Recovers His Loved Ones
      number: 1
      content: 'Now when David and his men came to Ziklag on the third day, the Amalekites
        had raided the Negev and Ziklag. When they attacked Ziklag, they burned it
        with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They took captive the women who were in it, from the youngest to
        the oldest. They did not kill anyone, but carried them off and went on their
        way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When David and his men came to the city, they saw, and it was burned
        with fire, and their wives, their sons, and their daughters had been taken
        captive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then David and the people who were with him raised their voices and
        wept until there was not enough strength in them to weep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Two of David\u2019s wives had been taken captive. Ahinoam from Jezreel
        and Abigail, the wife of Nabal the Carmelite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And David was in a very precarious situation, for the people spoke
        of stoning him, for the souls of all the people were bitter, each one over
        his sons and his daughters. But David strengthened himself in Yahweh his
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then David said to Abiathar the priest, the son of Ahimelech, \u201CPlease
        bring the ephod here for me.\u201D So Abiathar brought the ephod to David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And David inquired of Yahweh, saying, \u201CShould I pursue after
        this band of raiders? Will I overtake them?\u201D He said to him, \u201CPursue
        them, for you will certainly overtake them, and you will certainly rescue
        them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So David went, he and the six hundred men who were with him, and
        they came to the Wadi Besor, but the rest remained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'David pursued, he and four hundred men; but two hundred men stayed
        because they were too exhausted to pass over the Wadi Besor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then they found an Egyptian man in the open country and brought him
        to David, and they gave him food and he ate; they also gave him water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They gave him a slice of fig cake and two raisin cakes; he ate and
        this revived him, because he had not eaten food or drunk water for three
        days and three nights. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then David said to him, \u201CTo whom do you belong, and from where
        are you? The young man said, \u201CI am an Egyptian young man, a servant
        of an Amalekite man, but my master abandoned me because I became ill three
        days ago. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "We raided the Negev of the Kerethites and that which belongs to Judah
        and then the Negev of Caleb, and we burned Ziklag with fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So David asked him, \u201CWill you take me down to this band of raiders?\u201D
        He said, \u201CSwear to me by God that you will not kill me and that you
        will not deliver me into my master\u2019s hand! Then I will take you down
        to this band.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So he took him down, and there they were, spread out over the surface
        of all the land, eating and drinking and dancing because of all of the abundant
        plunder which they had taken from the land of the Philistines and from the
        land of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then David attacked them from twilight until the evening of the next
        day. Not a man of them escaped except four hundred young men who rode off
        on camels and fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So David recovered all that the Amalekites had taken; David also
        rescued his two wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'None of theirs was missing from the smallest to the greatest, even
        sons and daughters, from the plunder up to everything they had taken for
        themselves; David brought back everything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And David took all of the sheep, and the cattle they drove along
        in front of that livestock, and they said, \u201CThis is David\u2019s plunder.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then David came to the two hundred men who had been too exhausted
        to follow David; they had left them behind at the Wadi Besor. They went out
        to meet David and to meet the people who were with him. David came near with
        the people and asked them how they were doing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then all the corrupt and useless men among the men who went with
        David reacted and said, \u201CBecause they did not go with us, we will not
        give them anything from the plunder which we recovered, except each man may
        take his own wife and children. They must take them along and go!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But David said to them, \u201CYou should not do so, my brothers,
        with what Yahweh has given to us! He has preserved us and has given the raiding
        band that came against us into our hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And who would listen to you regarding this matter? For as the share
        of the one who went down into the battle, so the share of the one who remained
        with the baggage will be. They will share alike.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So from that day and beyond, he made it a rule and a regulation for
        Israel until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then David came to Ziklag, and he sent some of the plunder to the
        elders of Judah, to his friends, saying, \u201CHere is a gift for you from
        the plunder of the enemies of Yahweh!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'It was for those in Bethel, for those in Ramoth of the Negev, for
        those in Jattir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'for those in Aroer, for those in Siphmoth, for those in Eshtemoa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'for those in Racal, for those in the towns of the Jerahmeelites,
        for those in the towns of the Kenites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'for those in Hormah, for those in Bor Ashan, for those in Athach, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'for those in Hebron, and for all the places where David and his men
        had roamed.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul and Jonathan Die on Mount Gilboa'
      title: Saul and Jonathan Die on Mount Gilboa
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the Philistines were fighting against Israel, and the men of
        Israel fled before the Philistines, and they fell slain on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Philistines overtook Saul and his sons, and the Philistines
        killed Jonathan and Abinadab and Malki-Shua, the sons of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Saul was in the thick of the battle, and the archers spotted him,
        and he was badly wounded by the archers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Saul said to his armor bearer, \u201CDraw your sword and thrust
        me through with it, so that these uncircumcised do not come and thrust me
        through and make a fool of me!\u201D But his armor bearer was not willing
        to do so because he was very afraid. So Saul took the sword and fell on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when his armor bearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell on
        his sword and died with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Saul died, and his three sons, his armor bearer, and all his men
        together that same day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when the men of Israel who were on the other side of the valley
        and those who were beyond the Jordan saw that the men of Israel had fled
        and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned the towns and fled.
        Thus the Philistines came and lived in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And then the next day, the Philistines came to strip the dead and
        they found Saul and his three sons lying dead on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So they cut off his head and stripped off his armor. Then they sent
        messengers around in the land of the Philistines to proclaim victory in the
        temples of their idols and to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they put his armor in the temple of the Ashtoreth, and they fastened
        his corpse to the wall of Beth Shan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead heard about it, what the Philistines
        had done to Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'all of the valiant men set out and went all night and took the corpse
        of Saul and the corpses of his sons from the wall of Beth Shan, and they
        came to Jabesh and burned them there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they took their bones and buried them under the tamarisk in
        Jabesh, and they fasted for seven days. '
      comments: []
